nis players of Germany]]\n[[Category:Olympic tennis players of West Germany]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Mannheim]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Cross of the Order of Merit of the Federal Republic of Germany]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Olympic Order]]\n[[Category:Tennis players at the 1984 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Tennis players at the 1988 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Tennis players at the 1992 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:US Open (tennis) champions]]\n[[Category:West German expatriates in the United States]]\n[[Category:Wimbledon champions]]\n[[Category:World No. 1 tennis players]]\n[[Category:Grand Slam (tennis) champions in women's singles]]\n[[Category:Grand Slam (tennis) champions in women's doubles]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Silver Laurel Leaf]]\n[[Category:Germany's Sports Hall of Fame inductees]]\n[[Category:German philanthropists]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 1988 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 1992 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:People from SoHo, Manhattan]]\n", "name_user": "Barton Dave", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Steffi_Graf"}
{"title_page": "USS George M. Neal", "text_new": "{{Distinguish|text= {{USS|George H. McNeal|SP-312}}, a WWI [[minesweeper]]}}\n{{short description|Guided missile destroyer}}\n{|{{Infobox ship begin}}\n{{Infobox ship image\n|Ship image=File:USS George M. Neal (DDG-131) artist depiction.jpg\n|Ship caption=Graphical depiction of USS\u00a0''George M. Neal''\u00a0(DDG-131)\n}}\n{{Infobox ship career\n|Ship country={{nowrap|United States}}\n|Ship flag={{USN flag}}\n|Ship name=USS ''George M. Neal''\n|Ship namesake=[[George M. Neal]]\n|Ship awarded=27 September 2018<ref name=\"NVR\"/>\n|Ship builder=[[Huntington Ingalls Industries]]\n|Ship laid down=\n|Ship launched=\n|Ship commissioned=\n|Ship decommissioned=\n|Ship struck=\n|Ship sponsor=\n|Ship honors=\n|Ship fate=\n|Ship status=Authorized\n|Ship homeport=\n|Ship motto=\n|Ship badge = \n}}\n{{Infobox ship characteristics\n|Hide header=\n|Header caption=\n|Ship class={{sclass-|Arleigh Burke|destroyer}}\n|Ship displacement={{convert|9200|LT|abbr=on}}\n|Ship length={{convert|510|ft|abbr=on}}\n|Ship draft={{convert|33|ft|abbr=on}}\n|Ship propulsion=4 \u00d7 [[General Electric LM2500|General Electric LM2500-30]] [[gas turbine]]s, 2 shafts, {{convert|100000|shp|MW|lk=in|abbr=on}}\n|Ship range=\n|Ship complement=380 officers and enlisted\n|Ship sensors=\n|Ship EW=\n|Ship armament=*1 \u00d7 32 cell, 1 \u00d7 64 cell [[Mark 41 Vertical Launching System]], 96 \u00d7 [[RIM-66 Standard|RIM-66 SM-2]], [[BGM-109 Tomahawk]] or [[RUM-139 VL-Asroc]], missiles\n*1 \u00d7 [[5\"/54 caliber Mark 45 gun|{{convert|5|in|mm|abbr=on}}/62]], 2 \u00d7 [[M242 Bushmaster#Naval|25 mm Mk 38]], 4 \u00d7 [[M2 Browning|.50 cal (12.7 mm)]] guns\n*2 \u00d7 [[Mark 46 torpedo|Mk 46]] triple [[torpedo tube]]s\n*1 \u00d7 20&nbsp;mm [[Phalanx CIWS]]\n|Ship aircraft=2 \u00d7 [[SH-60 Sea Hawk]] helicopters\n|Ship aircraft facilities=Flight deck, Hangar bay\n|Ship notes=\n}}\n|}\n\n'''USS ''George M. Neal'' (DDG-131)''' is a planned {{sclass-|Arleigh Burke|destroyer|0}} [[guided missile destroyer]] of the [[United States Navy]], the 81st overall for the class.<ref name=\"NVR\">{{cite web | url={{NVR url|id=DDG131}} | title=George M. Neal (DDG 131) | publisher=[[Naval Vessel Register]] | accessdate=26 March 2019}}</ref> She will be named in honor of [[Aviation Machinist\u2019s Mate]] [[Petty officer third class|3rd Class]] George M. Neal, a [[Korean War]] veteran and [[prisoner of war]], who was a recipient of the [[Navy Cross]].<ref>{{cite press release |url=https://www.navy.mil/submit/display.asp?story_id=109029|title=SECNAV Names Destroyer in Honor of US Navy, Korean War Veteran|publisher=United States Navy|id=NNS190326-09|date=26 March 2019|accessdate=26 March 2019}}</ref> ''George M. Neal'' will be the sixth ship of the Flight III series.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n*{{NVR|{{NVR url|id=DDG131}}}}\n\n{{Arleigh Burke class destroyer}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:George M. Neal USS}}\n[[Category:Arleigh Burke-class destroyers]]\n[[Category:Proposed ships of the United States Navy]]\n\n{{US-mil-ship-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Distinguish|text= {{USS|George H. McNeal|SP-312}}, a WWI [[minesweeper]]}}\n{{short description|Guided missile destroyer}}\n{|{{Infobox ship begin}}\n{{Infobox ship image\n|Ship image=File:USS George M. Neal (DDG-131) artist depiction.jpg\n|Ship caption=Graphical depiction of USS\u00a0''George M. Neal''\u00a0(DDG-131)\n}}\n{{Infobox ship career\n|Ship country={{nowrap|United States}}\n|Ship flag={{USN flag}}\n|Ship name=USS ''George M. Neal''\n|Ship namesake=George M. Neal\n|Ship awarded=27 September 2018<ref name=\"NVR\"/>\n|Ship builder=[[Huntington Ingalls Industries]]\n|Ship laid down=\n|Ship launched=\n|Ship commissioned=\n|Ship decommissioned=\n|Ship struck=\n|Ship sponsor=\n|Ship honors=\n|Ship fate=\n|Ship status=Authorized\n|Ship homeport=\n|Ship motto=\n|Ship badge = \n}}\n{{Infobox ship characteristics\n|Hide header=\n|Header caption=\n|Ship class={{sclass-|Arleigh Burke|destroyer}}\n|Ship displacement={{convert|9200|LT|abbr=on}}\n|Ship length={{convert|510|ft|abbr=on}}\n|Ship draft={{convert|33|ft|abbr=on}}\n|Ship propulsion=4 \u00d7 [[General Electric LM2500|General Electric LM2500-30]] [[gas turbine]]s, 2 shafts, {{convert|100000|shp|MW|lk=in|abbr=on}}\n|Ship range=\n|Ship complement=380 officers and enlisted\n|Ship sensors=\n|Ship EW=\n|Ship armament=*1 \u00d7 32 cell, 1 \u00d7 64 cell [[Mark 41 Vertical Launching System]], 96 \u00d7 [[RIM-66 Standard|RIM-66 SM-2]], [[BGM-109 Tomahawk]] or [[RUM-139 VL-Asroc]], missiles\n*1 \u00d7 [[5\"/54 caliber Mark 45 gun|{{convert|5|in|mm|abbr=on}}/62]], 2 \u00d7 [[M242 Bushmaster#Naval|25 mm Mk 38]], 4 \u00d7 [[M2 Browning|.50 cal (12.7 mm)]] guns\n*2 \u00d7 [[Mark 46 torpedo|Mk 46]] triple [[torpedo tube]]s\n*1 \u00d7 20&nbsp;mm [[Phalanx CIWS]]\n|Ship aircraft=2 \u00d7 [[SH-60 Sea Hawk]] helicopters\n|Ship aircraft facilities=Flight deck, Hangar bay\n|Ship notes=\n}}\n|}\n\n'''USS ''George M. Neal'' (DDG-131)''' is a planned {{sclass-|Arleigh Burke|destroyer|0}} [[guided missile destroyer]] of the [[United States Navy]], the 81st overall for the class.<ref name=\"NVR\">{{cite web | url={{NVR url|id=DDG131}} | title=George M. Neal (DDG 131) | publisher=[[Naval Vessel Register]] | accessdate=26 March 2019}}</ref> She will be named in honor of [[Aviation Machinist\u2019s Mate]] [[Petty officer third class|3rd Class]] George M. Neal, a [[Korean War]] veteran and [[prisoner of war]], who was a recipient of the [[Navy Cross]].<ref>{{cite press release |url=https://www.navy.mil/submit/display.asp?story_id=109029|title=SECNAV Names Destroyer in Honor of US Navy, Korean War Veteran|publisher=United States Navy|id=NNS190326-09|date=26 March 2019|accessdate=26 March 2019}}</ref> ''George M. Neal'' will be the sixth ship of the Flight III series.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n*{{NVR|{{NVR url|id=DDG131}}}}\n\n{{Arleigh Burke class destroyer}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:George M. Neal USS}}\n[[Category:Arleigh Burke-class destroyers]]\