{"title_page": "Walter P. Thompson", "text_new": "{{Infobox Officeholder\n| honorific-prefix = \n| name             = Walter P. Thompson\n| honorific-suffix = {{Post-nominals|country=CAN|CC|size=100%}}\n| image            = \n| office           = [[Chancellor (education)|President]] of the [[University of Saskatchewan]]\n| predecessor      = [[James S. Thomson]]\n| successor        = [[John Spinks]]\n| term_start       = 1949\n| term_end         = 1959\n| birth_name       = Walter Palmer Thompson\n| birth_date       = {{birth date|1889|04|03}}\n| birth_place      = Decewsville, Ontario, Canada\n| death_date       = {{death date and age|1970|03|30|1889|04|03}}\n| death_place      = \n| spouse           = \n| party            = \n| relations        = \n| children         = \n| residence        = \n| alma_mater       = \n| occupation       = \n| profession       = \n| religion         = \n}}\n'''Walter Palmer Thompson''' {{Post-nominals|country=CAN|CC}} (April 3, 1889 &ndash; March 30, 1970) was a Canadian academic and former President of the [[University of Saskatchewan]].\n\n==Biography==\nBorn near [[Decewsville, Ontario]], he received a [[Bachelor of Arts|BA]] in 1910 from the [[University of Toronto]], an [[Master of Arts|MA]] in 1912 and a [[Ph.D.]] in 1914 both from [[Harvard University]]. In 1913 he joined the University of Saskatchewan as Professor and Head of the [[Biology]] Department. In 1934 he was appointed Dean of Junior Colleges; in 1938 he became Dean of Arts and Sciences; in 1942 he was Acting President; in 1948 he was Director of Summer School; and in 1949 he became President of the University. He retired in 1959. After he stepped down as university president, Thompson served as chair of the Advisory Planning Committee on Medical Care for the province of Saskatchewan.\n\nIn 1967 he was made a Companion of the [[Order of Canada]].\n\n==See also==\n*[[James Walter Thompson]]\n\n==References==\n* {{cite web | title=Walter P. Thompson (1949-1959) | work=University of Saskatchewan Archives | url=https://www.usask.ca/archives/history/president3.php | accessdate=April 26, 2005}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-npo|pro}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Harold Innis]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=President of the [[Royal Society of Canada]]|years=1947\u20131948}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Gustave Lanctot]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Thompson, Walter}}\n[[Category:1889 births]]\n[[Category:1970 deaths]]\n[[Category:Canadian university and college faculty deans]]\n[[Category:Harvard University alumni]]\n[[Category:Presidents of the University of Saskatchewan]]\n[[Category:Companions of the Order of Canada]]\n[[Category:University of Saskatchewan faculty]]\n[[Category:University of Toronto alumni]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Officeholder\n| honorific-prefix = \n| name             = Walter P. Thompson\n| honorific-suffix = {{Post-nominals|country=CAN|CC|size=100%}}\n| image            = \n| office           = [[Chancellor (education)|President]] of the [[University of Saskatchewan]]\n| predecessor      = [[James S. Thomson]]\n| successor        = [[John Spinks]]\n| term_start       = 1949\n| term_end         = 1959\n| birth_name       = Walter Palmer Thompson\n| birth_date       = {{birth date|1889|04|03}}\n| birth_place      = Decewsville, Ontario, Canada\n| death_date       = {{death date and age|1970|03|30|1889|04|03}}\n| death_place      = \n| spouse           = \n| party            = \n| relations        = \n| children         = \n| residence        = \n| alma_mater       = \n| occupation       = \n| profession       = \n| religion         = \n}}\n'''Walter Palmer Thompson''' {{Post-nominals|country=CAN|CC}} (April 3, 1889 &ndash; March 30, 1970) was a Canadian academic and former President of the [[University of Saskatchewan]].\n\n==Biography==\nBorn near [[Decewsville, Ontario]], he received a [[Bachelor of Arts|BA]] in 1910 from the [[University of Toronto]], an [[Master of Arts|MA]] in 1912 and a [[Ph.D.]] in 1914 both from [[Harvard University]]. In 1913 he joined the University of Saskatchewan as Professor and Head of the [[Biology]] Department. In 1934 he was appointed Dean of Junior Colleges; in 1938 he became Dean of Arts and Sciences; in 1942 he was Acting President; in 1948 he was Director of Summer School; and in 1949 he became President of the University. He retired in 1959. After he stepped down as university president, Thompson served as chair of the Advisory Planning Committee on Medical Care for the province of Saskatchewan.\n\nIn 1967 he was made a Companion of the [[Order of Canada]].\n\n==References==\n* {{cite web | title=Walter P. Thompson (1949-1959) | work=University of Saskatchewan Archives | url=https://www.usask.ca/archives/history/president3.php | accessdate=April 26, 2005}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[James Walter Thompson]]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Thompson, Walter}}\n[[Category:1889 births]]\n[[Category:1970 deaths]]\n[[Category:Canadian university and college faculty deans]]\n[[Category:Harvard University alumni]]\n[[Category:Presidents of the University of Saskatchewan]]\n[[Category:Companions of the Order of Canada]]\n[[Category:University of Saskatchewan faculty]]\n[[Category:University of Toronto alumni]]\n", "name_user": "LiteratureCompanion", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:add rsc succession box", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Walter_P._Thompson"}
{"title_page": "Ferd Dreher", "text_new": "{{distinguish|Ferdinand Dreher}}\n{{Infobox NFL biography\n|name=Ferd Dreher\n|image=\n|number=20\n|position=[[End (American football)|End]]\n|birth_date={{birth date|1913|2|23}}\n|birth_place=[[Jonesboro, Arkansas]]\n|death_date={{death date and age|1996|12|28|1913|2|23}}\n|death_place=[[Jonesboro, Arkansas]]\n|height_ft=6\n|height_in=3\n|weight_lbs=205\n|high_school=[[Jonesboro High School (Arkansas)|Jonesboro (AR)]]\n|college=[[Denver Pioneers football|Denver]]\n|draftyear=1938\n|draftround=12\n|draftpick=110\n|pastteams=\n* [[Chicago Bears]] ({{NFL Year|1938}})\n|nflnew=ferddreher/2513192\n|pfr=D/DrehFr20\n}}\n\n'''Ferdinand \"Ferd\" Adolphus Dreher''' (February 23, 1913 \u2013 December 28, 1996) was an [[American football]] [[End (American football)|end]] who played one season with the [[Chicago Bears]] of the [[National Football League]] (NFL). He was drafted by the Chicago Bears in the twelfth round of the [[1938 NFL Draft]]. He played [[college football]] at the [[University of Denver]] and attended [[Jonesboro High School (Arkansas)|Jonesboro High School]] in [[Jonesboro, Arkansas]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.pro-football-reference.com/players/D/DrehFr20.htm | title=Fred Dreher | publisher=Sports Reference LLC | work=pro-football-reference.com | accessdate=August 22, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==College career==\nDreher [[Letterman (sports)|lettered]] in football for the [[Denver Pioneers football|Denver Pioneers]] from 1936 to 1937, earning two first team all-conference awards. He recorded a team-high 30 points in 1936 and a second-best 35 points in 1937. He played basketball for the Pioneers from 1937 to 1938, helping the 1937 team to a 14-6 record while earning All-[[Rocky Mountain Conference]] honorable mention honors and also garnering third team All-[[Skyline Conference]] accolades in 1938. Dreher also participated in [[track and field]], winning the conference championships in the [[discus]] and [[shot put]] in 1937 and 1938. He played baseball in 1937. He earned seven letters as a Pioneer, two each in football, basketball and track while also earning one in baseball. Dreher was named the University of Denver Athlete of the Decade for the 1930s in May 1966. He was inducted into the University of Denver Athletics Hall of Fame in 2003.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.denverpioneers.com/sports/athletics/spec-rel/062907abk.html | title=University of Denver Athletics Hall of Fame Class of 2003 | publisher=denverpioneers.com | accessdate=August 22, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Professional career==\nDreher was selected by the [[Chicago Bears]] of the NFL with the 110th (and [[Mr. Irrelevant|final]]) pick in the [[1938 NFL Draft]]. He played in three games for the Bears during the [[1938 NFL season|1938 season]], recording 69 yards and one touchdown on three receptions.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.profootballarchives.com/dreh00200.html | title=Fred Dreher | publisher=profootballarchives.com | accessdate=August 22, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.justsportsstats.com/footballstatsindex.php?player_id=drehefre001 Just Sports Stats]\n\n{{Bears1938DraftPicks}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dreher, Ferd}}\n[[Category:1913 births]]\n[[Category:1996 deaths]]\n[[Category:Players of American football from Arkansas]]\n[[Category:American football ends]]\n[[Category:Denver Pioneers football players]]\n[[Category:Chicago Bears players]]\n[[Category:Denver Pioneers men's basketball players]]\n[[Category:American male discus throwers]]\n[[Category:American male shot putters]]\n[[Category:Denver Pioneers baseball players]]\n[[Category:People from Jonesboro, Arkansas]]\n[[Category:American men's basketball players]]\n", "text_old": "{{distinguish|Ferdinand Dreher}}\n{{Infobox NFL biography\n|name=Ferd Dreher\n|image=\n|number=20\n|position=[[End (American football)|End]]\n|birth_date={{birth date|1913|2|23}}\n|birth_place=[[Jonesboro, Arkansas]]\n|death_date={{death date and age|1996|12|28|1913|2|23}}\n|death_place=[[Jonesboro, Arkansas]]\n|height_ft=6\n|height_in=3\n|weight_lbs=205\n|high_school=[[Jonesboro High School (Arkansas)|Jonesboro (AR)]]\n|college=[[Denver Pioneers football|Denver]]\n|draftyear=1938\n|draftround=12\n|draftpick=110\n|pastteams=\n* [[Chicago Bears]] ({{NFL Year|1938}})\n|nflnew=ferddreher/2513192\n|pfr=D/DrehFr20\n}}\n\n'''Ferdinand \"Ferd\" Adolphus Dreher''' (February 23, 1913 \u2013 December 28, 1996) was an [[American football]] [[End (American football)|end]] who played one season with the [[Chicago Bears]] of the [[National Football League]] (NFL). He was drafted by the Chicago Bears in the twelfth round of the [[1938 NFL Draft]]. He played [[college football]] at the [[University of Denver]] and attended [[Jonesboro High School (Arkansas)|Jonesboro High School]] in [[Jonesboro, Arkansas]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.pro-football-reference.com/players/D/DrehFr20.htm | title=Fred Dreher | publisher=Sports Reference LLC | work=pro-football-reference.com | accessdate=August 22, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==College career==\nDreher [[Letterman (sports)|lettered]] in football for the [[Denver Pioneers football|Denver Pioneers]] from 1936 to 1937, earning two first team all-conference awards. He recorded a team-high 30 points in 1936 and a second-best 35 points in 1937. He played basketball for the Pioneers from 1937 to 1938, helping the 1937 team to a 14-6 record while earning All-[[Rocky Mountain Conference]] honorable mention honors and also garnering third team All-[[Skyline Conference]] accolades in 1938. Dreher also participated in [[track and field]], winning the conference championships in the [[discus]] and [[shot put]] in 1937 and 1938. He played baseball in 1937. He earned seven letters as a Pioneer, two each in football, basketball and track while also earning one in baseball. Dreher was named the University of Denver Athlete of the Decade for the 1930s in May 1966. He was inducted into the University of Denver Athletics Hall of Fame in 2003.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.denverpioneers.com/sports/athletics/spec-rel/062907abk.html | title=University of Denver Athletics Hall of Fame Class of 2003 | publisher=denverpioneers.com | accessdate=August 22, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Professional career==\nDreher was selected by the [[Chicago Bears]] of the NFL with the 110th (and [[Mr. Irrelevant|final]]) pick in the [[1938 NFL Draft]]. He played in three games for the Bears during the [[1938 NFL season|1938 season]], recording 69 yards and one touchdowns on three receptions.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.profootballarchives.com/dreh00200.html | title=Fred Dreher | publisher=profootballarchives.com | accessdate=August 22, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.justsportsstats.com/footballstatsindex.php?player_id=drehefre001 Just Sports Stats]\n\n{{Bears1938DraftPicks}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dreher, Ferd}}\n[[Category:1913 births]]\n[[Category:1996 deaths]]\n[[Category:Players of American football from Arkansas]]\n[[Category:American football ends]]\n[[Category:Denver Pioneers football players]]\n[[Category:Chicago Bears players]]\n[[Category:Denver Pioneers men's basketball players]]\n[[Category:American male discus throwers]]\n[[Category:American male shot putters]]\n[[Category:Denver Pioneers baseball players]]\n[[Category:People from Jonesboro, Arkansas]]\n[[Category:American men's basketball players]]\n", "name_user": "Zipcedric", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eProfessional career", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ferd_Dreher"}
{"title_page": "Subramanian Swamy", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=January 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2014}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n<!--NOTE: please do not add the title \"Dr\" to his name: see [[Wikipedia:Manual of Style (biographies)#Academic titles]]-->| office = [[Member of Parliament, Rajya Sabha]]\n| image = Subramanian Swamy.JPG\n| alt = \n| constituency = [[List of nominated members of Rajya Sabha|Nominated]]\n| constituency2 = [[Uttar Pradesh]]\n| party = [[Bharatiya Janata Party]] {{small|(2013\u2013present)}}\n| otherparty = [[Bharatiya Jana Sangh]] {{small|(1974\u20131977)}}<br/>[[Janata Party]] {{small|(1977\u20132013)}}\n| constituency1 = [[Uttar Pradesh]]\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1939|09|15|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Mylapore]], [[Madras Presidency]], [[British India]]<br/>(now in [[Tamil Nadu]], [[India]])\n| spouse = {{marriage|Roxna Swamy|1966}}\n| children = {{Plainlist|\n* Gitanjali Swamy\n* Suhasini Swamy Haidar \n }}\n| alma_mater = [[University of Delhi]] (BA)<br/>[[Indian Statistical Institute]] (MA)<br/>[[Harvard University]] (PhD)\n| occupation = Politician, economist, statistician\n| term_start = 26 April 2016\n| term_start1 = 1988\n| term_end1 = 1994\n| term_start2 = 1974\n| term_end2 = 1976\n| office3 = [[Ministry of Commerce and Industry (India)|Minister of Commerce and Industry]]\n| predecessor3 = \n| primeminister3 = [[Chandra Shekhar]]\n| successor3 = \n| term_start3 = 10 November 1990\n| term_end3 = 21 June 1991\n| office4 = [[Minister of Law and Justice (India)|Minister of Law and Justice]]\n| primeminister4 = [[Chandra Shekhar]]\n| term_start4 = 10 November 1990\n| term_end4 = 21 June 1991\n| predecessor4 = \n| successor4 = \n| office5 = [[Member of Parliament, Lok Sabha]]\n| term_start5 = 1998\n| term_end5 = 1999\n| constituency5 = [[Madurai (Lok Sabha constituency)|Madurai]]\n| predecessor5 = [[A. G. S. Ram Babu]]\n| successor5 = [[P. Mohan]]\n| term_start6 = 1977\n| term_end6 = 1984\n| constituency6 = [[Mumbai North East (Lok Sabha constituency)|Mumbai North East]]\n| predecessor6 = Rajaram Gopal Kulkarni\n| successor6 = [[Gurudas Kamat]]\n| office7 = President, [[Janata Party]]\n| term_start7 = 1990\n| term_end7 = 2013\n| website = [http://swamy39.blogspot.in/ Official Blog]\n}} \n'''Subramanian Swamy''' (born 15 September 1939) is an Indian [[politician]], [[economist]] and [[statistician]] who serves as a [[List of nominated members of the Rajya Sabha|nominated]] [[Member of Parliament, Rajya Sabha|Member of Parliament in Rajya Sabha]], the upper house of the [[Parliament of India|Indian Parliament]]. He is known for his [[Hindu nationalism|Hindu nationalist]] views.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|last=Anand|first=Geeta|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/07/02/world/asia/india-subramanian-swamy.html|title=Taking Down Politicians for Decades, and Rising in India\u2019s Government|date=2016-07-01|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-04-02|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.insidehighered.com/news/2011/12/08/harvard-kills-courses-controversial-summer-school-instructor|title=Harvard kills courses by controversial summer school instructor|website=www.insidehighered.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref name = \"removal\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/national/archive/2011/07/harvard-instructor-faces-removal-over-anti-muslim-op-ed/353487/|title=Harvard Instructor May Face Removal Over Anti-Muslim Op-Ed|last=Sehgal|first=Ujala|date=2011-07-30|website=The Atlantic|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> Swamy was a member of the [[Planning Commission (India)|Planning Commission of India]] and was a [[Union Council of Ministers|Cabinet Minister]] in the [[Chandra Shekhar]] government. Between 1994 and 1996, Swamy was Chairman of the Commission on Labour Standards and International Trade under [[List of Prime Ministers of India|former Prime Minister]] [[P. V. Narasimha Rao]].\n\nHe has written on foreign affairs of [[India]] dealing largely with [[China]], [[Pakistan]] and [[Israel]]. He was [[List of nominated members of Rajya Sabha|nominated]] to [[Rajya Sabha]] on 26 April 2016.\n\n==Early life and education==\nSubramanian Swamy was born in [[Mylapore]], [[Chennai]], [[Tamil Nadu]], India, to a family which hailed originally from [[Madurai]] in [[Tamil Nadu]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/analysis/column-the-paradox-called-subramanian-swamy-1567157 |title=The paradox called Subramanian Swamy |date=19 July 2011 |work=dna}}</ref><ref>[http://www.ibtl.in/news/exclusive/1221/subramanian/ Subramanian Swamy : Lets salute the real fighter 'SINGHAM]</ref> His father, Sitarama Subramanian, was a bureaucrat and his mother, Padmavathi, was a homemaker. He has one younger brother, Ram Subramanian as well as two younger sisters.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.firstpost.com/politics/subramanian-swamy-uncovered-doting-wife-leftist-brother-and-more-212638.html |title=Subramanian Swamy uncovered: Doting wife, leftist brother and more |work=Firstpost}}</ref>\n\nSitaraman Subramanian was an [[Civil Services of India|officer]] in the [[Indian Statistical Service]] who served as the director of the [[Central Statistical Organisation|Central Statistical Institute]] in [[Delhi]], and was a statistical adviser to the [[Government of India]].<ref name=\"Subramanian Swamy - Tehelka\"/> The family, which hailed from [[Madurai]] in [[Tamil Nadu]], moved to [[New Delhi]] when Swamy was only six months old. Due to his father's job and the family's [[Tamil language|Tamil]] roots, major national leaders like [[K. Kamaraj]], [[C. Rajagopalachari]] and [[S. Satyamurti]] often visited Sitaraman.<ref name=\"Swamy - Solution or Riddle\">{{cite web |title=The Jury Is Out, Subramanian Swamy: is the man a solution o\\r a riddle? |url=http://www.outlookindia.com/magazine/story/the-jury-is-out/279890 |work=[[Outlook (Indian magazine)|Outlook]] |accessdate=3 January 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"Swamy inscrutable\">{{cite web |title=The Outlier: The inscrutable politics of Subramanian Swamy |url=http://caravanmagazine.in/Story.aspx?Storyid=1389&StoryStyle=FullStory |work=[[The Caravan]] |accessdate=5 May 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120504172103/http://caravanmagazine.in/Story.aspx?Storyid=1389&StoryStyle=FullStory |archivedate=4 May 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"swamy queries\">{{cite web |title=Subramanian Swamy: Queries and Answers, Interview |url=http://www.rediff.com/news/report/why-should-i-dislike-chidambaram-subramanian-swamy/20120102.htm |accessdate=3 January 2012}}</ref>\n\nSwamy attended [[Hindu College, University of Delhi]], from where he earned his bachelor's degree in Mathematics. He then took his master's degree in Statistics from the [[Indian Statistical Institute]], [[Kolkata]]. He was later recommended by [[Hendrik S. Houthakker]]<ref name=\"Swamy inscrutable\"/> and went to study at [[Harvard University]] on a full [[Rockefeller]] scholarship,<ref name=\"Swamy inscrutable\"/> where he received his PhD in Economics in 1965, with his thesis titled ''Economic Growth and Income Distribution in a Developing Nation''.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.genealogy.math.ndsu.nodak.edu/id.php?id=208481 |title = Subramanian Swamy - the Mathematics Genealogy Project}}</ref> His thesis adviser was [[Nobel laureate]] [[Simon Kuznets]].<ref name=\"Swamy inscrutable\"/><ref name=\"Guru PhD: Swamy\">{{cite web |title=An Indian tribute: Paul Samuelson, Guru |url=http://business.rediff.com/special/2009/dec/17/subramanian-swamy-pays-tribute-to-paul-samuelson.htm |accessdate=29 December 2011}}</ref> While he was a doctoral student at Harvard, he attended [[Massachusetts Institute of Technology]] as a cross-registered student<ref name=\"Swamy Samuelson\">{{cite news |url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/opinion/subramanian-swamy-samuelson-a-genius-who-was-my-guru-109122200056_1.html |title=Subramanian Swamy: Samuelson - A genius who was my guru|publisher=[[Business Standard]]|newspaper=Business Standard India|date=22 December 2009|last1=Swamy|first1=Subramanian}}</ref> and later worked at the [[United Nations Secretariat]] in [[New York City]] as an Assistant Economics Affairs Officer in 1963. He subsequently worked as a resident tutor at [[Lowell House]] at Harvard University.<ref name=\"Harvard economist enemity\">{{cite web |title=Harvard Economist Accused of 'Spreading Enmity Between Communities' |url=https://www.thecrimson.com/flyby/article/2011/10/5/indian-india-swamy-current/ |publisher=[[Harvard Crimson]], Flyby The blog of The Harvard Crimson|accessdate=14 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Academic career==\nIn July 1965, immediately after obtaining his PhD in economics from [[Harvard]], Swamy joined the Department of Economics at the [[Harvard Faculty of Arts and Sciences]] as an assistant professor.<ref name=\"Swamy inscrutable\"/><ref name=\"Swamy recovery IITD\">{{cite web |url=http://zeenews.india.com/news/nation/hc-swamy-s-plea-for-recovery-of-dues-from-iit_760640.html |title=High Court of Delhi : Swamy's plea for recovery of dues from IIT |publisher=[[Zee News]] |accessdate=27 February 2012}}</ref> In 1969, he was made an associate professor.<ref name=\"Harvard removes Subramanian Swamy's courses over controversial column\">{{cite web |url=http://www.indiaeducationreview.com/news/harvard-removes-subramanian-swamys-courses-over-controversial-column |title=Harvard removes Subramanian Swamy's courses over controversial column |publisher=Indiaeducationreview}}</ref> As associate professor, he was invited by [[Amartya Sen]]<ref name=\"Subramanian Swamy - Tehelka\">{{cite web |url=http://archive.tehelka.com/story_main51.asp?filename=Ne311211Coverstory.asp |title=The Beastly Beatitudes: The rise, fall and resurrection of Subramanian Swamy}}</ref> to occupy the chair on Chinese studies at the [[Delhi School of Economics]].<ref name=\"Swamy - Solution or Riddle\"/> He accepted the offer and even travelled to India to take up the position, but his appointment was cancelled at the last minute due to his views on India's economic policy and also its nuclear policy.<ref name=\"Subramanian Swamy - Tehelka\"/> At that time, [[Socialism in India|India was still partially oriented towards socialism]] and the \"command economy\" model instituted by [[Nehru]], and Swamy was a believer in market economy.\n\nThereafter, Swamy moved to the [[Indian Institute of Technology, Delhi]] and he was a full Professor of Mathematical Economics there from 1969 to the early 1970s.<ref name=\"Swamy recovery IITD\"/><ref name=\"Swamy Rediff\">{{cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/news/1998/mar/17sswamy.htm |title=The Rediff Special: The Man People Love to Hate |publisher=[[Rediff.com]]}}</ref> He was removed from the position by its board of governors in the early 1970s but was legally reinstated in the late 1990s by the [[Supreme Court of India]]. He continued in the position until 1991 when he resigned to become a cabinet minister. He served on the Board of Governors of the IIT, Delhi (1977\u201380) and on the Council of IITs (1980\u201382). He also taught economics courses at [[Harvard Summer School]]<ref>{{cite news |author=Special Correspondent |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/article1455140.ece |title=Swamy to teach at Harvard |location=Chennai |work=The Hindu |date=15 February 2011}}</ref> until 2011, when the Harvard faculty voted to eliminate Swamy's courses as a result of his \"offensive\" statements about Muslims.<ref name=\":1\"/><ref name = \"removal\"/>\n\nSwamy now serves as Chairman of the [[School of Communication and Management Studies]] in [[Kochi]].<ref name=SCMSMgmt>{{cite web |title=Management |url=http://scmsgroup.org/php/showContent.php?linkid=295&partid=2 |work=SCMS Group of Institutions |publisher=SCMS Group}}</ref><ref name=In.com>{{cite web |title=Politician Subramanian Swamy |url=http://www.in.com/subramanian-swamy/profile-262171.html |work=In.com India |publisher=In.com (web18)}}</ref>\n\n==Political career==\n\n===Early politics===\nSwamy's career started with his involvement in the Sarvodaya movement, which was an apolitical movement but which formed the foundation of the creation of [[Janata Party]] later.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://janataparty.org/articledetail.asp?rowid=8 |title=My Experiences with Jayaprakash Narayan&nbsp;\u2014 Subramanian Swamy |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120828044859/http://janataparty.org/articledetail.asp?rowid=8 |archivedate=28 August 2012 |publisher=Janata Party Website}}</ref> The real turn in his political career came after his sacking from IIT. Liberal economic policies put forward by him did not go well with the then Prime Minister [[Indira Gandhi]] who sneered at his plans as 'Santa Claus with unrealistic ideas'. He was later expelled from [[Indian Institute of Technology]]. This marked the beginning of his active political career. Staunch opponent of Indira Gandhi [[Bharatiya Jana Sangh]] sent him to [[Rajya Sabha]] \u2013 the upper house of Indian Parliament.<ref name=\"Subramanian Swamy - Tehelka\"/>\n\nHe was elected Member of Parliament 5 times between 1974 and 1999. He has twice represented the city of Mumbai North East during 1977 and 1980, Uttar Pradesh and Tamil Nadu in the Parliament.<ref name=\"Subramanian Swamy - Tehelka\"/>\n\nDuring the period of the [[Indian Emergency|Emergency]], he fled to the United States, seeking haven with an Indian businessman in [[Michigan]] who had become the spokesperson of the opposition in the United States. In 1976, when the Emergency was still in force and an arrest warrant had been issued in his name, Swamy came to Parliament to attend the session and managed to escape India after the session was adjourned. This act of defiance was well received in the eyes of opposition parties.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sunday-guardian.com/investigation/animosity-between-pc-swamy-spans-decades |title=Animosity between PC, Swamy spans decades |publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://newindianexpress.com/states/tamil_nadu/Cables-Swamy-an-ultranationalist/2013/04/13/article1542610.ece |title=Cables: Swamy, an ultranationalist |work=The New Indian Express}}</ref>\n\nSwamy was one of the founding members of the [[Janata Party]] and served as its president till 2013.\n\n===Electoral history ===\n1974\u201376 - Member of [[Rajya Sabha]] from [[Uttar Pradesh]], elected on a [[Jan Sangh]] party ticket <br/>\n1977-80 - Member of [[Lok Sabha]] from [[Mumbai North East (Lok Sabha constituency)|Mumbai North-East]], elected on a [[Janata Party]] ticket <br/>\n1980-84 - Member of [[Lok Sabha]] from [[Mumbai North East (Lok Sabha constituency)|Mumbai North-East]], elected on a [[Janata Party]] ticket <br/>\n1988\u201394 - Member of [[Rajya Sabha]] from [[Uttar Pradesh]], elected on a [[Janata Party]] ticket <br/>\n1998-99 - Member of [[Lok Sabha]] from [[Madurai (Lok Sabha constituency)|Madurai]], elected on a [[Janata Party]] ticket <br/>\n2016 - Member of [[Rajya Sabha]], [[List of nominated members of Rajya Sabha|Nominated Category]]\n\n===Minister of Commerce and Law of India===\nDuring 1990 and 1991, Swamy served as a member of the [[Planning Commission (India)|Planning Commission of India]] and as Cabinet Minister of Commerce and Law. Albeit uncorroborated, During this period, Swamy claims to have provided the blueprint for the [[Economic liberalisation in India|economic reforms in India]] under Prime Minister [[Chandra Shekhar]]<ref name=\"Wither India Reform\">{{cite news |title=Whither economic reforms? India |url=http://www.frontline.in/static/html/fl1719/17190780.htm |publisher=[[Frontline (magazine)|Frontline, The Hindu]] |accessdate=7 January 2012 |location=Chennai, India}}</ref><ref name=\"Swamy India Reform\"/> which was later carried out in 1991 by [[Manmohan Singh]],<ref name=\"Swamy inscrutable\"/> then Finance Minister under leadership of Prime Minister [[Narasimha Rao]].<ref name=\"Swamy India Reform\">{{cite web |title=Assessing India's economic reforms: Swamy |url=http://www.frontlineonnet.com/fl1902/19020610.htm |publisher=Frontline, The Hindu |accessdate=12 October 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111127052246/http://www.frontlineonnet.com/fl1902/19020610.htm |archivedate=27 November 2011}}</ref> In the Narasimha Rao government, Swamy was Chairman of the Commission on Labour Standards and International Trade, which was a Cabinet-rank post.<ref>http://www.dnaindia.com/india/report-subramanian-swamy-demands-bharat-ratna-for-p-v-narasimha-rao-2046472</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/why-subramanian-swamy-should-determine-whether-to-be-an-asset-or-liability-for-modi-government/articleshow/53023135.cms |title = Why Subramanian Swamy should determine whether to be an asset or liability for Modi government|newspaper = The Economic Times|date = 3 July 2016|last1 = Mukhopadhyay|first1 = Nilanjan}}</ref>  In his book, Swamy asserts that Manmohan Singh acknowledges his role as well.<ref name=\"Swamy - SCMS Group Chair\">{{cite web |url=http://scmsgroup.org/php/showContent.php?linkid=295&partid=2 |title=Board of Management of the SCMS Group of Educational Institutions: Chairman Subramanian Swamy}}</ref><ref name=\"shfe\">{{cite book |title=Financial Architecture and Economic Development in China and India |publisher=Konark Publishers Pvt Ltd |isbn=978-81-220-0718-3}}</ref>\n\n===Later years===\n[[File:The book \"Moditva \u2013 the Idea behind the Man\" being launched by Rajnath Singh.jpg|thumb|250px|right|Swamy at launching a book with BJP members in 2014.]]\nBetween 1994 and 1996, Swamy was chairman of the Commission on Labour Standards and International Trade (equivalent in rank to a cabinet minister) under Prime Minister [[P. V. Narasimha Rao]].<ref name=\"Subramanian Swamy - Tehelka\"/> He continued to be president of the Janata Party till 2013. On 11 August 2013, Swamy officially joined [[Bharatiya Janata Party|BJP]] when its president was Rajnath Singh. His admission to the party would mark the merger of the Janata Party with the Bharatiya Janata Party.<ref name=\"indianexpress1\">{{cite web |url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/subramanian-swamys-janta-party-merges-with-bjp/1153983/?socialmedia |title=Subramanian Swamy's Janta Party merges with BJP |work=The Indian Express |date=11 August 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Court petitions==\n\n===Petition to strike down anti-defamation laws===\nIn Oct 2014, Swamy filed a petition in Supreme Court praying for declaring Sections 499 and 500 of the Indian Penal Code that deal with criminal defamation  as unconstitutional.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://supremecourtofindia.nic.in/outtoday/wr18414p-2014_10_30.pdf |title=SUPREME COURT OF INDIA RECORD OF PROCEEDINGS |work=Su |publisher=Supreme Court of India |accessdate=2016-01-18 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160507144638/http://supremecourtofindia.nic.in/outtoday/wr18414p-2014_10_30.pdf |archivedate=7 May 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n===Complaint against Jayalalithaa===\nIn 1996, Swamy had filed a criminal complaint against [[Jayalalithaa]] which led to [[Disproportionate Asset case against Jayalalithaa|her prosecution]], conviction and sentencing to four years imprisonment by the trial court in 2014.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/live-jayalalithaa-wealth-case-verdict/article6452086.ece |title=Jayalalithaa conviction: As it happened |newspaper=The Hindu |access-date=2017-02-19 |language=en}}</ref> Later, on May 11, 2015, a special Bench of the [[Karnataka High Court]] set aside the trial court order convicting former Tamil Nadu Chief Minister Jayalalitha, who was acquitted of all charges in the disproportionate assets case.<ref>{{cite news |title=Dr. Subramanian Swamy vs J. Jayalalitha on 20 August 1996 |url=http://indiankanoon.org/doc/1137705/}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Jayalalithaa guilty in assets case, Gets 4-year jail term |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/jayalalithaa-verdict-assets-case-disproportionate-special-court/1/393035.html |publisher=India Today |date=27 September 2014 |location=Bangalore |accessdate=27 September 2014}}</ref> An Appeal against the High court verdict was filed in Supreme Court.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.ndtv.com/tamil-nadu-news/supreme-court-to-hear-karnatakas-plea-against-jayalalithaas-acquittal-1231332 |title=Supreme Court to Hear Karnataka's Plea Against Jayalalithaa's Acquittal |work=NDTV |date=2015-10-12 |accessdate=2016-01-18}}</ref> However, keeping personal differences aside, he wished her a speedy recovery on her recent illness and advised she visit [[Singapore]] for treatment.<ref>{{cite tweet |user=Swamy39 |author=Subramanian Swamy |number=779332399838572544 |date=23 September 2016 |title=JJ should take my advice to charter a plane and go to Singapore for medical attention. We may be opponents but wish her long life and health}}</ref> The final verdict of Supreme Court came in February, 2017 that indicted [[Jayalalithaa|Jayalalitha]] posthumously and upheld the trial court judgement [[wikt:in toto|in toto]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/Jayalalithaa-Sasikala-criminally-conspired-at-Poes-Garden-to-launder-ill-gotten-wealth-SC/article17301596.ece |title=Jayalalithaa, Sasikala criminally conspired at Poes Garden to launder ill-gotten wealth: SC |last=Rajagopal |first=Krishnadas |newspaper=The Hindu |access-date=2017-02-19 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n===Phone tapping allegation===\n\nSwamy released a letter alleging that former intelligence chief had asked [[Department of Telecommunications|DoT]] to [[Phone tapping|tap the phone]] of many politicians and businessmen in [[Karnataka]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Watch-out-Your-phone-may-be-tapped/articleshow/1190723.cms?referral=PM |title=Watch out! Your phone may be tapped |work=The Times of India}}</ref> when [[Ramakrishna Hegde]], the then Chief Minister, resigned in 1988.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Repository/getFiles.asp?Style=OliveXLib:LowLevelEntityToPrint_TOINEW&Type=text/html&Locale=english-skin-custom&Path=TOIBG/2010/04/26&ID=Ar01501 |title=Phone-tapping allegations forced Hegde to quit in '88 |publisher=}}</ref> Hegde then filed a case against him in 1989 and 1990.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://indiankanoon.org/doc/1559770/ |title=Dr. Subramaniam Swamy vs Ramakrishna Hegde on 18 October, 1989 |publisher=}}</ref><ref>[http://judis.nic.in/supremecourt/imgs1.aspx?filename=39307] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131219001856/http://judis.nic.in/supremecourt/imgs1.aspx?filename=39307|date=19 December 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://supremecourtofindia.nic.in/scr/2012_v5_piv.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-12-18 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130818204917/http://supremecourtofindia.nic.in/scr/2012_v5_piv.pdf |archivedate=18 August 2013 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n===Hashimpura massacre===\n{{Main|Hashimpura massacre}}\nIn 1987, when Muslim youths were killed under police custody, Swamy spoke against it and sat on a fast for more than a week in Jantar Mantar demanding the institution of an inquiry.<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.dailypioneer.com/columnists/item/51993-why-is-bjp-always-doing-congress-a-favour?.html |title=Why is BJP always doing Congress a favour? |periodical=[[The Pioneer (Indian newspaper)|Daily Pioneer]] |date=14 July 2012 |author=Shahroze Tariq Raza |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120716233544/http://www.dailypioneer.com/columnists/item/51993-why-is-bjp-always-doing-congress-a-favour?.html |archivedate=16 July 2012}}</ref> After 25 years he started pursuing the case once again in court.<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.oneindia.com/2012/07/10/subramanian-swamy-gets-weapon-against-chidambaram-riot-1032579.html |title=Subramanian Swamy gets brahmastra against Chidambaram |periodical=[[Oneindia.in|News One India]] |date=10 July 2012}}</ref>\n\nRebecca John, a counsel for the Hashimpura complainants, told Additional Sessions Judge Rakesh Siddhartha who is conducting the trial in the case, that \"there is no other motive than politics behind Swamy's plea for further investigation and it would only further delay the trial\".<ref>{{cite web |author=TNN |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-01-08/india/36215347_1_hashimpura-subramanian-swamy-janata-party-president |title=Hashimpura massacre case: Victims oppose Subramanian Swamy's plea for further probe |work=The Times of India |date=8 January 2013 |access-date=19 January 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130119181437/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-01-08/india/36215347_1_hashimpura-subramanian-swamy-janata-party-president |archive-date=19 January 2013 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n===Role in exposing 2G spectrum case===\n{{main|2G spectrum case}}\nIn November 2008, Swamy amongst others wrote the first of five letters to Prime Minister [[Manmohan Singh]] seeking permission to prosecute [[A. Raja]] in regard to [[2G spectrum case]].<ref>{{cite news |title=2G chronology |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/India-news/NewDelhi/Chronology-of-events-in-the-2G-scam-case/Article1-805604.aspx |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120824100351/http://www.hindustantimes.com/India-news/NewDelhi/Chronology-of-events-in-the-2G-scam-case/Article1-805604.aspx |archivedate=24 August 2012}}</ref> After not receiving any response,<ref name=\"spectrum corruption\">{{cite web |title=2G Spectrum Shadiness |url=http://www.caravanmagazine.in/Story/615/Spectrum-Shadiness.html |work=[[The Caravan]] |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101130091658/http://caravanmagazine.in/Story/615/Spectrum-Shadiness.html |archivedate=30 November 2010 |accessdate=5 May 2012}}</ref> Swamy decided to file a case on his own in the [[Supreme Court of India]] regarding the matter, which then asked the [[Central Bureau of Investigation]] to produce a detailed report on it.<ref>{{citation |periodical=The Hindu |date=6 February 2011 |accessdate=1 August 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/2011/02/06/stories/2011020659910600.htm |title=CBI asked to file detailed report on 2G scam |author=Jiby Kattakayam |location=Chennai, India |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110825071135/http://www.hindu.com/2011/02/06/stories/2011020659910600.htm |archivedate=25 August 2011 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> He further called on the Indian government to re-auction the [[2G]] spectrum without the involvement of Communications Minister [[Kapil Sibal]].<ref>{{citation |url=http://in.news.yahoo.com/auction-2g-spectrum-restrain-sibal-subramanian-swamy-20110110-034015-410.html |title=Re-auction 2G spectrum, restrain Sibal: Subramanian Swamy |agency=[[Indo-Asian News Service]] |date=11 January 2011 |accessdate=1 August 2011}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 April 2011, he filed a 206-page petition with PM Singh seeking permission to prosecute [[Sonia Gandhi]] on charges of corruption. He also raised doubts regarding her acquisition of Indian citizenship.<ref>{{citation |url=http://newindianexpress.com/states/tamil_nadu/article383222.ece |periodical=The New Indian Express |title=Permit me to prosecute Sonia: Swamy |date=19 April 2011 |accessdate=1 August 2011}}</ref> Swamy filed documents in the court to prosecute [[Minister for Home Affairs (India)|Minister of Home Affairs]] [[P. Chidambaram]] by including a 15 January 2008 letter written by Chidambaram to Prime Minister Manmohan Singh. Swamy also placed on record the certified copy of the minutes of a meeting between Chidambaram, Raja and the prime minister during the tenure of Raja as the MOC&IT.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics/nation/2g-case-subramanian-swamy-submits-documents-against-chidambaram-arguments-on-january-21/articleshow/11399259.cms |title=2G case: Subramanian Swamy submits documents against Chidambaram, arguments on January 21 |work=The Economic Times |date=7 January 2012 |accessdate=7 January 2012}}</ref> Since criminal charges were filed against the accused, but no evidence was given by Swamy or the CBI, all the respondents have got bail as of July 2012.\n\n====Sanction to prosecute telecom minister A. Raja====\nOn 31 January 2012, the [[Supreme Court of India]] accepted Swamy's petition against the [[Prime Minister's Office (India)|Prime Minister's Office]] in the 2G case, saying that all public authorities should give a sanction within three months against any public official if a request is made for prosecution.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/2g-case-sc-allows-swamys-petition-on-grant-of-sanction/articleshow/11696767.cms|title=2G case: SC allows Swamy's petition on grant of sanction|date=2012-01-31|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2020-01-01}}</ref>\n\nThe Supreme Court said that Swamy had the [[locus standi]] to seek sanction from the Prime Minister for the prosecution of [[A Raja]] in the 2G case. Sanction by a competent authority for the prosecution of a public servant has to be granted within a time frame, the apex court said. Justice [[AK Ganguly]] said that the sanction would be deemed to be granted if competent authority failed to take a decision within four months.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Prosecuting-corrupt-officials-SC-sets-deadline-for-govt/articleshow/11696857.cms|title=Prosecuting corrupt officials: SC sets deadline for govt {{!}} India News - Times of India|last=Jan 31|first=PTI {{!}} Updated|last2=2012|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2020-01-01|last3=Ist|first3=12:08}}</ref>\n\nSwamy's arguments were that he wrote to the PMO on 29 November 2008, but it was only on 19 March 2010 the PMO replied that the plea made by Swamy was \"premature\" as investigation was being carried out by the [[Central Bureau of Investigation]] (CBI).\nRaja was arrested by the CBI in the case and got bail on 15 May 2012 after spending nearly 15 months in the [[Tihar Jail|Tihar Central Jail]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/article3421102.ece |location=Chennai |work=The Hindu |title=Raja gets bail, walks out of Tihar jail |date=15 May 2012}}</ref>\n\nOn December 21, 2017, the special CBI Court Judge acquitted the accused including [[Andimuthu Raja]].<ref>[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/2g-scam-verdict-today/liveblog/62187750.cms 2G scam case: All accused acquitted]</ref>\n\n=== Petition to strike down \"single directive provision\" ===\nIn 1997, Swamy filed a petition in the [[Supreme Court of India]] to strike down a provision which barred [[Central Bureau of Investigation|CBI]] from investigating corruption charges against officers of the rank of joint secretary and above without prior permission of the [[Govt of India]] called as ''\"Dr. Subramanian Swamy Versus Director, Central Bureau of Investigation & Anr.\"''<ref name=\"With govt's single directive, law no longer above all\">{{cite news |title=With govt's single directive, law no longer above all |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/With-govts-single-directive-law-no-longer-above-all/articleshow/1019946.cms |accessdate=6 May 2014}}</ref> On 6 May 2014, a five-judge [[Constitution Bench (India)|constitution bench]] held the single directive provision as invalid and unconstitutional. The court said that \"Protection of prior approval for probing graft charges against officers at level of joint secretary and above has propensity of shielding corruption\"<ref>{{cite news |title=CBI can investigate corruption charges against top babus without govt nod: SC |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/CBI-can-investigate-corruption-charges-against-top-babus-without-govt-nod-SC/articleshow/34726114.cms |accessdate=6 May 2014 |date=6 May 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"Supreme Court Judgement in WRIT PETITION (CIVIL) NO. 38 OF 1997\">{{cite web |title=Supreme Court Judgement in WRIT PETITION (CIVIL) NO. 38 OF 1997 |url=http://sci.nic.in/outtoday/41503.pdf |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140506183826/http://sci.nic.in/outtoday/41503.pdf |archivedate=2014-05-06}}</ref> Experts such as former CBI Director Joginder Singh praised the judgement as \"Superb\".<ref name=\"Experts hail Supreme Court's decision\">{{cite news |title=Experts hail Supreme Court's decision |url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ani/experts-hail-supreme-court-s-decision-on-investigating-officers-of-jt-secretary-rank-114050601408_1.html |accessdate=6 May 2014}}</ref> Incumbent CBI Director [[Ranjit Sinha]] welcomed the judgement and said, \"now a very heavy responsibility has been cast upon us to ensure that no innocent civil-servant is harassed.\"<ref name=\"CBI welcomes Supreme Court decision\">{{cite news |title=CBI welcomes Supreme Court decision |url=http://www.aninews.in/newsdetail2/story167291/cbi-welcomes-supreme-court-decision-on-investigating-officers-of-jt-secretary-rank.html |accessdate=6 May 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140511030532/http://www.aninews.in/newsdetail2/story167291/cbi-welcomes-supreme-court-decision-on-investigating-officers-of-jt-secretary-rank.html |archivedate=11 May 2014 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n===Investigation on EVM===\n{{further|Indian voting machines}}\n\nSwamy demanded that an independent committee should be formed to check the security and safety of the [[Indian voting machines|Electronic Voting Machines]] (EVM) to avoid any rigging or tampering. He demanded that a printed receipt should be given to every voter after casting the vote.<ref>{{cite news |author=Special Correspondent |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/swamy-for-expert-panel-on-secure-evms/article106271.ece |title=Swamy for expert panel on secure EVMs |location=CHENNAI |work=The Hindu |date=13 February 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/evms-not-tamperfree/article712729.ece |title=EVMs not tamper-free |newspaper=The Hindu |date=18 February 2010}}</ref> His [[Public-interest litigation (India)|PIL]] to investigate the working of EVM was dismissed by the [[Delhi High Court]] on 17 January 2012. The court refused to give any direction to the [[Election Commission of India|Election Commission]] to bring back paper-ballot system or use of printed receipts. The Commission argued that the use of paper is not feasible due to the huge size of Indian electorate. The court further asked the Election Commission to \"immediately begin a process of wider consultations\" and the Parliament \"to go into this question in depth and decide\".<ref>{{cite web |author=Anita |url=http://www.oneindia.com/2012/01/17/delhi-hc-says-not-impossible-to-tamper-evm-s.html |title=Delhi High Court says not impossible to tamper EVMs |publisher=OneIndia |date=17 January 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/delhi-hc-rejects-swamys-plea-to-bring-back-paper-ballots/900646 |title=Delhi HC rejects Swamy's plea to bring back paper ballots |work=The Indian Express |date=17 January 2012}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 January 2013 the [[Election Commission of India|Election Commission]] informed the [[Supreme Court of India|Supreme Court]] that it would include [[Voter-verified paper audit trail|Voter Verifiable Paper Audit Trail]] (VVPAT) system which is in the testing phase after the court agreed with some points raised by Swamy who was the contender,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://supremecourtofindia.nic.in/outtoday/9093.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-10-10 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303231056/http://supremecourtofindia.nic.in/outtoday/9093.pdf |archivedate=3 March 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> in the machines so that every voter will come to know who he/she is voting by getting a printed slip after pressing the EVM button.<ref>{{cite web |author=PTI |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Voter-to-get-paper-receipt-after-casting-ballot-EC-tells-SC/articleshow/18134882.cms?referral=PM |title=Voter to get paper receipt after casting ballot: EC tells SC |work=The Times of India |date=22 January 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=Legal Correspondent |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/voter-paper-trail-in-phases-ec/article4333597.ece |title=Voter paper trail in phases: EC |newspaper=The Hindu |date=23 January 2013}}</ref> The voter paper audit trail has then been in use from 4 September 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.jagranjosh.com/current-affairs/ec-to-use-voter-verifiable-paper-audit-trail-vvpat-system-in-nagaland-bypolls-1376729528-1 |title=EC to use Voter Verifiable Paper Audit Trail (VVPAT) System in Nagaland by-polls |work=Jagranjosh.com|date=17 August 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-newdelhi/new-delhi-voters-can-verify-who-they-voted-for/article5362745.ece |title=New Delhi voters can verify who they voted for |newspaper=The Hindu|date=18 November 2013 }}</ref>\n\nOn 8 October 2013 the Supreme Court directed the Election Commission to implement audit trail system in [[2014 Indian general election|2014 general election]] in phases.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.jagranjosh.com/current-affairs/supreme-court-1381300734-1 |title=Supreme Court Directed Election Commission to Install VVPAT System in EVMs for 2014 Polls |work=Jagranjosh.com|date=9 October 2013 }}</ref>\n\n===National Herald case ===\n{{Main|National Herald Case}}\nOn 1 November 2012 Swamy alleged that both [[Sonia Gandhi|Sonia]] and [[Rahul Gandhi]] have committed fraud and [[land grabbing]] to a tune of {{INRConvert|20|b}} by acquiring a public ltd company called Associated Journals Private Ltd (AJPL) through their owned private company, Young Indian<ref>{{cite web |url=http://indianexpress.com/article/explained/national-herald-case-where-the-matter-stands/ |title=National Herald case explained: Everything that you need to know |publisher=[[The Indian Express]] |date=8 December 2015}}</ref> which was formed on 23 November 2010.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/congress-to-revive-national-herald-challenges-swamy-to-take-it-to-court/article4058571.ece |title=Congress to revive National Herald, challenges Swamy to take it to court |newspaper=[[The Hindu]] |date=3 November 2015|last1=Gupta |first1=Smita }}</ref> Through this they had got publication rights of ''[[The National Herald (India)|National Herald]]'' and ''[[Qaumi Awaz]]'' newspapers, with real estate properties in Delhi and Uttar Pradesh.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/national-herald-case-enforcement-directorate-mulling-probe-possibility/article7959871.ece |title=National Herald case: Enforcement Directorate mulling probe possibility |newspaper=[[The Hindu]] |date=8 December 2015|last1=Pandey |first1=Devesh K. }}</ref> The acquired place was intended only for newspaper purposes but were used for running a passport office, amounting to [[Crore|crores]] of rupees, it alleges.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/wealth/personal-finance-news/national-herald-case-heres-how-much-associated-journals-seven-properties-worth/articleshow/50165303.cms|title=National Herald case: Here's how much Associated Journals' seven properties worth|last=Babar|first=Kailash|date=2015-12-14|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2020-01-01|last2=Sharma|first2=Ravi Teja}}</ref> Swamy further added that Rahul Gandhi hid the facts in his affidavit while filing nomination for the [[2009 Indian general election|2009 Lok Sabha elections]].<ref>{{cite web |author=Sanjay Singh |url=http://www.firstpost.com/politics/swamy-does-a-kejriwal-targets-sonia-rahul-for-landgrab-511644.html |title=Swamy does a Kejriwal, targets Sonia & Rahul for landgrab |publisher=Firstpost |date=1 November 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=New Delhi, 1 Nov 2012, DHNS |url=http://www.deccanherald.com/content/289449/swamy-accuses-sonia-rahul-property.html |title=Swamy accuses Sonia, Rahul of property fraud |work=Deccan Herald |date=1 November 2012}}</ref>\n\nIt further alleges that on 26 February 2011 AJPL approved the transfer of [[Unsecured debt|unsecured loan]] of {{INRConvert|900|m}} from the [[All India Congress Committee]] at zero interest.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/rahul-threatens-to-sue-subramanian-swamy/article4055087.ece |title=Rahul threatens to sue Subramanian Swamy |newspaper=[[The Hindu]] |date=2 November 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indiatoday.in/story/national-herald-case-sonia-gandhi-rahul-will-have-to-appear-in-court/1/540297.html |title=National Herald case: Sonia Gandhi, Rahul will have to appear in court |publisher=[[India Today]] |date=7 December 2015}}{{dead link|date=May 2016|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref> Swamy argued that it is illegal for any political party to lend the loan as per violation of Section 269T of Income Tax Act 1961.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/what-is-the-national-herald-case-all-about/1/541733.html |title=What is the National Herald case all about? |publisher=[[India Today]] |date=8 December 2015}}</ref> On 2 November, the party responded that the loan was given only for reviving National Herald newspaper with no commercial interest.<ref>{{cite news |author=Smita Gupta |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/congress-to-revive-national-herald-challenges-swamy-to-take-it-to-court/article4058571.ece |title=Congress to revive National Herald, challenges Swamy to take it to court |newspaper=The Hindu |date=2 November 2012}}</ref> Swamy decided to approach the Supreme Court for de-recognising the Congress party, while the Election Commission ordered the probe on 17 November 2012.<ref>{{cite news |agency=Press Trust of India |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/swamy-to-move-court-against-ec/article4073917.ece |title=Swamy to move court against EC |work=The Hindu |date=7 November 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.news18.com/news/politics/ec-orders-probe-against-rahul-gandhi-for-wrong-information-522167.html |title=EC orders probe against Rahul Gandhi for 'wrong information' about his assets- Politics News- Politics-IBNLive |publisher=Ibnlive.in.com |date=17 November 2012}}</ref>\n\nThe hearing of the case had been taken up thereafter on different occasions<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.oneindia.com/2013/03/16/subramanian-swamy-s-victory-against-sonia-rahul-gandhi-1173225.html |title=Subramanian Swamy's victory against Sonia, Rahul Gandhi |publisher=One India |date=16 March 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dailypioneer.com/nation/national-herald-acquisition-delhi-court-summons-roc-to-testify-records.html |title=NATIONAL HERALD ACQUISITION: DELHI COURT SUMMONS ROC TO TESTIFY RECORDS |publisher=dailypioneer |date=29 April 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"ZEE NEWS\">{{cite web |url=http://zeenews.india.com/news/nation/court-summons-sonia-gandhi-rahul-in-national-herald-land-grab-case_942922.html |title=Court summons Sonia Gandhi, Rahul in National Herald land grab case |publisher=ZEE NEWS |date=26 June 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/National-Herald-case-Delhi-HC-stays-criminal-proceedings-against-Sonia-Gandhi-Rahul-Gandhi/articleshow/39756755.cms |title=National Herald case: Delhi HC stays criminal proceedings against Sonia Gandhi, Rahul Gandhi |publisher=TIMES OF INDIA |date=6 August 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://zeenews.india.com/news/nation/national-herald-case-relief-for-sonia-rahul-delhi-hc-stays-summons-till-august-13_952910.html |title=National Herald case: Relief for Sonia, Rahul, Delhi HC stays summons till August 13 |publisher=ZEE NEWS |date=6 August 2014}}</ref> with the court observing [[prima facie]] evidence against all the accused.<ref name=\"ZEE NEWS\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/news/report/national-herald-case-what-you-should-know/20151209.htm |title=National Herald case: What you should know |publisher=[[Rediff.com]] |date=9 December 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://indianexpress.com/article/explained/national-herald-case-where-the-matter-stands/ |title=National Herald case explained: Everything you need to know |publisher=[[The Indian Express]] |date=10 December 2015}}</ref> On 1 August 2014 the [[Enforcement Directorate]] initiated probe to find any [[Money laundering#India|money laundering]] in the case<ref>{{cite web |url=http://zeenews.india.com/news/nation/national-herald-case-trouble-for-sonia-rahul-as-ed-begins-preliminary-probe_951680.html |title=National Herald case: Trouble for Sonia, Rahul as ED begins preliminary probe |publisher=ZEE NEWS |date=1 August 2014}}</ref> while on the same day Swamy was served notice by the High Court.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/national-herald-case-delhi-high-court-serves-notice-to-subramanian-swamy-congress-sonia-gandhi-rahul-gandhi/1/375130.html |title=National Herald case: Delhi High Court serves notice to Subramanian Swamy |publisher=INDIA TODAY |date=1 August 2014}}</ref> On 28 August the metropolitan court fixed 9 December for the next hearing of the case,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.firstpost.com/politics/national-herald-case-delhi-trial-court-to-hear-case-on-9-december-1686177.html |title=National Herald case: Delhi trial court to hear case on 9 December |publisher=FIRST POST |date=28 August 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.oneindia.com/india/court-defers-hearing-in-national-herald-case-1510868.html |title=Court defers hearing in National Herald case |publisher=ONE INDIA |date=28 August 2014}}</ref> while on 12 January 2015 the judge of the Delhi High Court recused himself from hearing the case stating that schedule of cases has been changed and directed that the petitions be directed before an appropriate bench.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-others/national-herald-case-judge-recuses-from-hearing-sonia-gandhi-rahul-gandhi-plea/ |title=National Herald case: Judge recuses from hearing Sonia Gandhi, Rahul Gandhi plea |publisher=THE INDIAN EXPRESS |date=12 January 2015}}</ref> On 27 January 2015, the Supreme Court asked Swamy to make out a case for the speedy trial in the Delhi High Court since the petition cannot be heard directly.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.firstpost.com/politics/national-herald-case-sc-directs-subramanian-swamy-approach-delhi-hc-2067027.html |title=National Herald case: SC directs Subramanian Swamy to approach Delhi HC |publisher=FIRST POST |date=27 January 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 September 2015 it was reported that the Enforcement Directorate had reopened the investigation.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.news18.com/news/politics/enforcement-directorate-reopens-national-herald-case-involving-sonia-and-rahul-gandhi-which-was-closed-in-august-1102471.html |title=Enforcement Directorate reopens National Herald case involving Sonia and Rahul Gandhi, which was closed in August |publisher=IBN Live |date=18 September 2015}}</ref> Following it, on 19 December 2015 Patiala House Court granted unconditional bail immediately on the hearing to all the five accused but one.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/gandhis-get-bail-in-herald-case/article8008532.ece |title=Sonia, Rahul get bail, hit out at Modi |newspaper=[[The Hindu]] |date=19 December 2015|last1=Kumar |first1=Nirnimesh |last2=Iqbal |first2=Mohammed |last3=Jeelani |first3=Mehboob }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://in.reuters.com/article/india-gandhis-sonia-rahul-congress-idINKBN0U208Z20151219 |title=Sonia, Rahul Gandhi get bail after rare court date over alleged fraud |publisher=Reuters India |date=19 December 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/india/live-national-herald-case-sonia-rahul-gandhi-to-appear-before-court-2157431 |title=National Herald case: Sonia, Rahul Gandhi immediately get bail; next hearing on February 20 |publisher=[[Daily News and Analysis]] |date=19 December 2015}}</ref> On 12 July 2016 the Delhi High Court set aside the trial court order of 11 January<ref>{{cite web |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/National-Herald-case-Relief-for-Congress/articleshow/53172103.cms |title=National Herald case: Relief for Congress |publisher=[[Times of India]] |date=12 July 2016}}</ref> and 11 March<ref>{{cite web |url=http://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-news-india/national-herald-case-delhi-court-asks-for-balance-sheets-of-ajl-congress/ |title=National Herald case: Delhi Court asks for balance sheets of AJL, Congress |publisher=[[The Indian Express]] |date=12 March 2016}}</ref> based on plea by Swamy to examine balance sheets of Congress party, [[Associated Journals Ltd|AJL]] and Young Indian from 2010-2013,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://delhihighcourt.nic.in/writereaddata/upload/Announcements/AnnouncementFile_BE5FNPPV.PDF |title=J- 2 PRONOUNCEMENT OF JUDGEMENTS(APPLET. JURISDICTION),1.CRL.M.C 671/2016,2.CRL.M.C. 672/2016, 3.CRL.M.C. 1317/2016, 4. CRL.M.C.1319/2016, 5. CRL.M.C.1321/2016 |publisher=[[Delhi High Court]] |date=12 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-news-india/national-herald-case-congress-hopes-delhi-high-court-ruling-will-end-bjp-subramanian-swamys-celebrations-2910408/ |title=National Herald case: Congress hopes Delhi High Court ruling will end BJP, Subramanian Swamy's celebrations |publisher=[[The Indian Express]] |date=12 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://zeenews.india.com/news/india/why-is-congress-so-afraid-of-national-herald-papers-will-re-apply-for-same-subramanian-swamy_1908050.html |title=Why is Congress so afraid of National Herald papers? Will re-apply for documents: Subramanian Swamy |publisher=[[Zee News]] |date=17 July 2016}}</ref> and fixed the date of next hearing on 20 August.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/pti-stories/will-file-fresh-application-in-herald-case-swamy-to-court-116071600485_1.html |title=Will file fresh application in National Herald case: Subramanian Swamy to court |publisher=[[Business Standard]] |date=16 July 2016}}</ref>\nCurrently, the case proceedings are on-going in Delhi High Court.<ref>https://www.livelaw.in/news-updates/i-have-no-documents-to-prove-that-rent-was-paid-to-young-india-152248</ref>\n\n===Temple Cases===\n====Nataraja temple case====\n\nSwamy had filed a petition in the Supreme Court with priests of the dikshithar sect challenging the decision of the [[Madras High Court]] on transferring the administration of the [[Thillai Nataraja Temple, Chidambaram|Nataraja temple]] to the then Tamil Nadu government in 2009.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ndtv.com/south/tamil-nadu-government-will-not-manage-famous-temple-rules-supreme-court-546936 |title=Tamil Nadu government will not manage famous temple, rules Supreme Court |author=J Sam Daniel Stalin |date=6 January 2014 |work=NDTV.com}}</ref>\n\nSwamy on referring to the provisions of Tamil Nadu Hindu Religious and Charitable Endowments Act, contended that [[Smarta Tradition|Podu Dikshitars]] have right to administer the temple<ref>{{cite web |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Nataraja-temple-to-be-managed-by-priest-not-by-Tamil-Nadu-govt/articleshow/28474693.cms |title=Nataraja temple to be managed by priest, not by Tamil Nadu govt |work=The Times of India}}</ref> and argued on handing over the administration on mismanagement grounds of temple's wealth is violation under article \n26 of the Constitution of India.<ref>http://judis.nic.in/supremecourt/imgs1.aspx?filename=41133</ref> On 6 January 2014 the Supreme Court ruled that the administration is to be handed over back to the priests of the temple from the state government.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/states/tamil_nadu/Nataraja-Temple-to-be-Managed-by-Priest-not-by-Tamil-Nadu-Government/2014/01/06/article1985968.ece#.UxyM0D-Syiw |title=Nataraja Temple to be Managed by Priest not by Tamil Nadu Government |work=The New Indian Express}}</ref>\n====Removing State control on Hindu temples====\nSubramanian Swamy filed a petition to remove  Kerala State government's control over Hindu temples by abolishing [[Devaswom boards in Kerala|Devaswom]]. In 2018, the Supreme Court agreed to examine the petition moved by him and TG Mohan Das to abolish Devaswom Board.The Supreme Court issued notice to the Kerala government and Devaswom Board of Travanacore and Cochin and sought their response in six weeks.<ref>http://www.newindianexpress.com/states/kerala/2018/oct/13/supreme-court-issues-notice-to-kerala-on-devaswom-board-1884903.html</ref> In 2019, the Kerala government opposed Subramanian Swamy's plea.<ref>https://wap.business-standard.com/article/pti-stories/kerala-opposes-swamy-s-plea-to-make-devaswom-boards-free-of-state-s-control-119012301349_1.html</ref>\n\n====Ayodhya temple case====\n\n{{Further|Ram Janmabhoomi}}\n{{Main|Ayodhya dispute}}\n\nOn 22 February 2016, Swamy filed a petition in the Supreme Court allowing construction of [[Rama]] temple at the disputed site where [[Demolition of the Babri Masjid|Babri Masjid was demolished]] in 1992, and expediting the adjudication related to order of the Allahabad High Court on 30 September 2010,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/article8268416.ece |title=Allow 'rebuilding' of Ram temple, Swamy urges SC |publisher=[[The Hindu]] |date=23 February 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/subramanian-swamy-moves-supreme-court-to-build-ram-temple-in-ayodhya/articleshow/51087635.cms |title=Subramanian Swamy moves Supreme Court to build Ram temple in Ayodhya |publisher=[[The Economic Times]] |date=23 February 2016}}</ref> petition was accepted on 26 February to be later heard by the court.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/sc-allows-swamys-plea-to-rebuild-ram-temple-along-with-ramjanmabhoomi-appeals/article8285368.ece |title=SC agrees to hear plea to 'rebuild' Ram temple |publisher=[[The Hindu]] |date=26 February 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Campaign against black money==\n{{see also|Black money in India}}\nSwamy founded the Action Committee Against Corruption in India (ACACI) on 14 October 2011 and acted as a chairperson. ACACI's goal is to take action against corruption in government and against [[Indian black money]] stashed abroad.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://indianexpress.com/tag/acaci/ |title=ACACI - The Indian Express |publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Swamy-announces-panel-against-corruption/articleshow/10355742.cms?referral=PM |title=Swamy announces panel against corruption |work=The Times of India}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.india.com/top-n/black-money-list-subramanian-swamy-lists-6-steps-to-bring-back-black-money-in-an-open-letter-to-narendra-modi-186813/ |title=Black Money List: Subramanian Swamy lists 6 steps to bring back black money in an open letter to Narendra Modi |author=Shikhar Jiwrajka |work=India.com}}</ref>\n\n==Views==\n\n===Foreign policy===\n==== China ====\n<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Deng Xioping with Subramanian Swamy 1981.jpg|thumb|right|[[Vice Chairman of the Communist Party of China]] [[Deng Xiaoping]] with Swamy at Great Hall of the People at Beijing in 1981.{{deletable image-caption|Tuesday, 10 October 2017|PROD}}]] -->\nSwamy has worked towards normalising [[Sino-Indian relations|relations between China and India]]. According to Swamy, the re-opening of the [[Mount Kailash#Religious significance|Kailash Mansarovar pilgrimage]] route was announced at a meeting convened by the People's Republic of China paramount leader [[Deng Xiaoping]] in April 1981, in which Swamy was in attendance. This meeting was widely reported in the media, although such claims have been contested by supporters of former Prime Minister [[Atal Bihari Vajpayee]].{{citation needed|date=December 2017}}\n\n==== Israel ====\nIn various speeches and articles, Swamy has expressed his admiration for, and solidarity with, the [[State of Israel]] and has credited its retaliatory capacity for its ability to survive as a nation in a hostile Arab environment. Swamy made pioneering efforts towards India's establishment of [[India\u2013Israel relations|diplomatic relations with Israel]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/first-israel-visas-from-india-were-issued-from-this-mps-residence/articleshow/59438603.cms |title=First Israel visas in India were issued from this MP's residence}}</ref> In 1982, Swamy became the first Indian political leader to make a well-publicised trip to Israel, where he met with several important Israeli leaders such as [[Yitzhak Rabin]] and then-Prime Minister [[Menachem Begin]]. His efforts at normalising relations with Israel have borne fruit with both India as well as Israels decision, in 1992, to facilitate the building of embassies in their respective countries.<ref name=\"Subramanian Swamy Party President\">{{cite web |url=http://janataparty.org/president.html |title=His Role in Foreign Affairs:The President |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121013034757/http://janataparty.org/president.html |archivedate=13 October 2012}}</ref>\n\n==== Sri Lanka and LTTE ====\nSwamy, on several occasions, has voiced support for the state of Sri Lanka in its role during [[Sri Lankan Civil War|Sri Lanka's protracted civil war with the LTTE]], for which he was criticised as \"pro Lanka\" by his political opponents domestically.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.news18.com/news/politics/india-shouldnt-support-resolution-against-lanka-swamy-454333.html |title=India shouldn't support resolution against Lanka: Swamy |work=IBNLive}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/sri-lankan-tamils-issue-karunanidhi-enacting-drama-says-jayalalithaa-dmk-pull-out-from-upa/1/258563.html |title=Karunanidhi enacting drama, says Jayalalithaa on DMK pull-out from UPA |publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sundayobserver.lk/2013/09/08/fea03.asp |title=Think as Sri Lankans first |publisher= |accessdate=25 July 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160506221510/http://www.sundayobserver.lk/2013/09/08/fea03.asp |archivedate=6 May 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://zeenews.india.com/news/nation/swamy-slams-dmk-chief-for-remarks-on-indo-sri-lankan-relations_793425.html |title=Swamy slams DMK chief for remarks on Indo-Sri Lankan relations |work=Zee News}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/india/subramanian-swamy-attacked-by-lawyers-in-madras-hc/story-KiCd6SNSbJ9pIT8a3mW0QN.html |title=Subramanian Swamy attacked by lawyers in Madras HC |publisher=[[Hindustan Times]]}}</ref> In an interview given to ''[[The Sunday Leader]]'' newspaper, Swamy stated that the Indian government should attend the [[CHOGM]] meeting held in [[Colombo]] despite stiff opposition from Indian politicians in Tamil Nadu concerned for the welfare and human rights of Tamils in Sri Lanka, placing the onus on the LTTE for human rights violations during the Sri Lankan civil war,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thesundayleader.lk/2013/11/03/india-must-ignore-lttes-financial-orphans-dr-subramanium-swamy/ |title=India Must Ignore LTTE's Financial Orphans \u2013 Dr Subramanium Swamy |publisher=}}</ref><ref>[http://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/pm-may-skip-chogm-meet-due-to-opposition/article1-1148937.aspx] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131111051031/http://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/pm-may-skip-chogm-meet-due-to-opposition/article1-1148937.aspx|date=11 November 2013}}</ref> he had favoured [[Mahinda Rajapaksa]] also  during [[2015 Sri Lankan presidential election|Sri Lanka 2015 election]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://zeenews.india.com/news/nation/give-rajapaksa-bharat-ratna-for-wiping-out-ltte_757861.html |title=Give Rajapaksa Bharat Ratna for wiping out LTTE |publisher=ZEE NEWS |date=11 February 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Tamil-activists-burn-Subramanian-Swamys-effigy-after-he-demands-Bharat-Ratna-for-Rajapaksa/articleshow/44899410.cms |title=Tamil activists burn Subramanian Swamy's effigy after he demands Bharat Ratna for Rajapaksa |publisher=TIMES OF INDIA |date=21 October 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.itnnews.lk/local-news/large-fraction-of-tamils-will-vote-for-president-rajapaksa-subramaniam-swamy/ |title=Large fraction of Tamils will vote for President Rajapaksa \u2013 Subramaniam Swamy |publisher=itnnews.lk |date=28 November 2014 |access-date=13 August 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160823030745/http://www.itnnews.lk/local-news/large-fraction-of-tamils-will-vote-for-president-rajapaksa-subramaniam-swamy/ |archive-date=23 August 2016 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n==== United States ====\nSwamy is a strong supporter of U.S. President [[Donald Trump]], endorsing Trump's presidential candidacy in 2016 and comparing Trump to himself.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2016-05-24/modi-s-bet-on-trump-of-india-signals-risks-to-his-reform-push |title=Modi's Bet on 'Trump of India' Signals Risks to Reform Push |work=[[Bloomberg News|Bloomberg]] |date=May 24, 2016}}</ref>\n\nAfter the [[Unite the Right rally|Charlottesville riots]] in August 2017, he posted a tweet urging Indians residing in the United States to \"stand with Trump at this hour of his being hunted by cockeyed liberals & Left wing loonies on racism\" and praised Trump for \"having showed the hypocrites their place by telling it like it is.\"<ref>https://www.thequint.com/neon/social-buzz/subramanian-swamy-trolled-on-twitter</ref>\n\nFollowing criticism of Pakistan by Trump, Swamy called for closer relations between India and the United States.<ref>http://www.freepressjournal.in/india/after-us-president-trumps-anti-pak-tweet-subramanian-swamy-calls-for-stronger-india-us-relations/1197599</ref>\n\n===Domestic policy===\n==== Kashmir ====\nIn September 2008, Swamy stridently retorted against the contentions of some Indian columnists who voiced their opinions in favor of \"peacefully\" surrendering Kashmir to Pakistan. He said,\n\n:\"I would say that the silent suffering majority of India wants none of this. The 'Kashmir issue,' in fact, can no more be solved by dialogue either with the Pakistanis or the Hurriyat, leave alone the constitutional impossibility of allowing it to secede. [...]Kashmir, in fact, is now our [[History of Kashmir|defining identity]]. It is a touchstone for our resolve to preserve our national integrity. The population of that State may be majority Muslim but the land and its history is predominantly Hindu. For our commitment to the survival of the ancient civilisation of India and the composite culture that secularists talk of, we have not only to win that coming inevitable war but also resolve never to part with Kashmir. [...]\n\n:Pakistanis often cite the United Nations resolutions on Kashmir to argue for a plebiscite. This obfuscates the fact of accession of the State to India. The legality of the Instrument of Accession signed in favour of India by the then Maharaja of J&K, Hari Singh, on 26 October 1947 has to prevail anyway.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-opinion/article1345324.ece |location=Chennai, India |work=The Hindu |title=Kashmir defines Indian identity |date=25 September 2008}}</ref>\n\n==== Tamil Nadu politics ====\nSwamy is well known for his critical views against the \"Aryan versus Dravidian\" politics of [[Periyar E. V. Ramasamy]], calling it as the theory forwarded by the British.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hindu.com/2011/06/18/stories/2011061862200200.htm |title=Tamil Nadu / Madurai News : \"Caste not birth-based\" |work=The Hindu |date=18 June 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130806095535/http://www.hindu.com/2011/06/18/stories/2011061862200200.htm |archivedate=6 August 2013 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> He has been a staunch opponent of the armed rebel group [[Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam]].<ref>{{cite news |agency=Press Trust of India |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Janata-Party-chief-Subramanian-Swamy-appears-before-tribunal-examining-LTTE-ban/articleshow/6828953.cms?referral=PM |title=Janata Party chief Subramanian Swamy appears before tribunal examining LTTE ban |work=The Times of India |date=28 October 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/ltte-part-of-the-problem-swamy/article1375090.ece |title=LTTE part of the problem: Swamy |work=The Hindu |date=13 November 2008}}</ref><ref>[http://www.epdpnews.com/articals_content.php?artiid=24&artiname=Subramanian%20Swamy%20addresses%20the%20Sri%20Lankan%20Diaspora%20in%20Toronto&ln=eng] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120510114143/http://www.epdpnews.com/articals_content.php?artiid=24&artiname=Subramanian%20Swamy%20addresses%20the%20Sri%20Lankan%20Diaspora%20in%20Toronto&ln=eng|date=10 May 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/nation/article157835.ece |title=Swamy criticises Karuna's statement on refugees |publisher=NEW INDIAN EXPRESS |date=16 May 2012}}</ref>\nHe also urged the Indian government not to support the US led resolution condemning [[Alleged war crimes during the final stages of the Sri Lankan Civil War|war crimes]] in the [[Sri Lankan Civil War]], citing it as one-sided and not in the interest of India.<ref>{{cite news |agency=Press Trust of India |url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2013-03-08/news/37561573_1_subramanian-swamy-unhrc-rajapaksa |title=Subramanian Swamy asks US to work with Sri Lanka on resolution at UNHRC |work=The Economic Times |date=8 March 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://channelone.co.in/India/india-should-not-support-resolution-against-sri-lanka--subramanian-swamy-839.html |title=India should not support resolution against Sri Lanka: Subramanian Swamy |publisher=Channel One |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131109124814/http://channelone.co.in/India/india-should-not-support-resolution-against-sri-lanka--subramanian-swamy-839.html |archivedate=9 November 2013}}</ref> Swamy moved the court and got the order restoring quota for [[Sri Lankan Tamil people|Sri Lankan Tamil]] refugees in colleges in the state.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/states/tamil_nadu/Higher-Education-Remains-a-Struggle-for-Refugees/2014/06/22/article2293215.ece |title=Higher Education Remains a Struggle for Refugees |publisher=NEW INDIAN EXPRESS |date=22 June 2014}}</ref>\n\nSwamy obtained [[Supreme Court of India|Supreme Court]] Stay against the implementation of [[Sethusamudram Shipping Canal Project]] (SSCP). He believes that it would hurt the sentiments of people who believe that this shallow land connecting between [[Tamil Nadu]] and [[Sri Lanka]] was built by Lord [[Rama]]. He strongly opposes the implementation of SSCP citing that implementing this scheme will be a criminal offence under section 295 [[Indian Penal Code]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/india/report_ram-setu-project-is-illegal-arbitrary-and-unacceptable-subramanian-swamy_1804422 |title=Ram Setu project is illegal, arbitrary and unacceptable: Subramanian Swamy |agency=ANI |date=25 February 2013 |accessdate=23 July 2013 |publisher=DNA}}</ref><ref>[http://www.indlaw.com/guest/DisplayNews.aspx?FCD913AA-4308-4C14-9B32-F8696B16303F] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140303155432/http://www.indlaw.com/guest/DisplayNews.aspx?FCD913AA-4308-4C14-9B32-F8696B16303F|date=3 March 2014}}</ref> He wrote letters to Prime Minister of India in June 2009 asking him to stop the project<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tamil.oneindia.com/news/2009/06/18/tn-hold-sethu-project-implementation-says-swamy.html |title=Hold Sethu project implementation, says Swamy, \u0b9a\u0bc7\u0ba4\u0bc1.. '\u0bb9\u0bcb\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bcd \u0b86\u0ba9\u0bcd': \u0b9a\u0bbe\u0bae\u0bbf |publisher=OneIndia Tamil |language=Tamil |date=18 June 2009 |accessdate=16 October 2011}}</ref> and had informed the Supreme Court on 14 October 2015 that the government may not continue with the [[Sethusamudram Shipping Canal Project|Sethusamudram Project]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/govt-decided-not-to-touch-ram-sethu-subramanian-swamy-tells-supreme-court/article7758406.ece |title=Govt. decided not to \"touch\" Ram Sethu, Swamy tells SC |publisher=[[The Hindu|THE HINDU]] |date=14 October 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Anti-Muslim views ===\nIn response to the [[2011 Mumbai bombings]], he wrote an editorial in ''[[Daily News and Analysis]]'' (''DNA'') where he called for the demolition of mosques and for the disenfranchisement of Muslims unless \"acknowledge that their ancestors were Hindus\".<ref name=\":0\" /> \nSome of Swamy's suggestions in the article are:\n\n*The Hindu is the target and that Muslims of India are being programmed by a slow reactive process to become radical and thus slide into suicide against Hindus.\n*Remove Article 370, and re-settle ex-servicemen in the Valley. Create Panun Kashmir for Hindu Pandit community. Look or create opportunity to take over PoK. If Pakistan continues to back terrorists, assist the Baluchis and Sindhis to struggle for independence.\n*Enact a national law prohibiting conversion from Hindu religion to any other religion.\n*Only Muslims who \"acknowledge that their ancestors were Hindus\" be allowed to vote in India.<ref>{{citation |author=Subramanian Swamy |date=16 July 2011 |accessdate=27 July 2011 |title=Analysis: How to wipe out Islamic terror |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/analysis/analysis_how-to-wipe-out-islamic-terror_1566203-all |work=[[DNA (newspaper)|DNA]] |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110818232314/http://www.dnaindia.com/analysis/analysis_how-to-wipe-out-islamic-terror_1566203-all |archivedate=18 August 2011}}</ref>\n\nSwamy had written a similar column in ''[[The New Indian Express]]'' after the [[2008 Mumbai attacks]].  As a result of his \"reprehensible\" views in the articles, [[Harvard University]] cancelled two economics courses taught at the university by Swamy.<ref name=BBCNews20150628>\n{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-india-16081751 |title=Harvard drops Indian MP Subramanian Swamy's courses |publisher=BBC News |date=December 8, 2011 |accessdate=2015-06-28}}</ref><ref name=\":1\" />\n\nOn 3 August 2011 the [[National Commission for Minorities]] decided to file civil charges against Swamy for the article and promoting on the basis of religion.<ref>{{cite web |author=Vidya Subrahmaniam |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/minorities-commission-to-press-criminal-charges-against-swamy/article2317169.ece |title=Minorities' commission to press criminal charges against Swamy |work=The Hindu |date=3 August 2011}}</ref> On 4 October 2011 the [[Delhi Police]] registered the case.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/case-against-swamy/article2510624.ece |title=Case against Swamy |work=The Hindu |date=4 October 2011}}</ref> Swamy was then granted police protection by the [[Delhi High Court]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/swamy-gets-interim-protection/article2800800.ece |title=Swamy gets interim protection |work=The Hindu |date=14 January 2012}}</ref> On 30 January 2012 Swamy was granted [[anticipatory bail]] by the court with the condition that he would not write such articles in the future.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Subramanian-Swamy-granted-anticipatory-bail-in-inflammatory-article-case/articleshow/11684787.cms |title=Subramanian Swamy granted anticipatory bail in 'inflammatory' article case |work=The Times of India |date=30 January 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nSwamy met Roxna Kapadia, whose father was member of [[Indian Civil Service (British India)]] and an Indian lady of [[Parsi]] ethnicity who was studying PhD in mathematics at [[Harvard University]].<ref>{{cite web |author=Elizabeth Roche |url=http://www.livemint.com/Leisure/J7Ot7WsW7O8cytA908g5zJ/Perfect-copetitioners.html |title=Perfect co-petitioners |publisher=Livemint |date=8 February 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"Roxna Swamy Interview\">{{cite web |title=The well-regarded Supreme Court advocate on her husband : SUNIT ARORA INTERVIEWS ROXNA SWAMY |url=http://www.outlookindia.com/magazine/story/his-views-are-those-of-a-patriotic-indian/279891 |work=[[Outlook (Indian magazine)|Outlook]] |accessdate=3 January 2012}}</ref> They were married in June 1966. Swamys have two daughters. The elder daughter, Gitanjali Swamy, is an entrepreneur and private equity professional. She is married to [[Sanjay Sarma]], a professor at [[MIT]], who is the son of E.A.S Sarma, a retired [[IAS officer]] and former secretary Economic Affairs to the government of India. The younger daughter, Suhasini Haidar, is a print and television journalist married to Nadeem Haidar, the son of former Indian Foreign Secretary [[Salman Haider|Salman Haidar]].{{citation needed|date=February 2017}}\n\n==Honours and awards==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%;\"\n|-\n! Year !! Name !! Awarding organisation !! Ref.\n|-\n| 2012\n| Distinguished Alumni Award.\n| [[Hindu College, University of Delhi]].\n|<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/article2799252.ece |title=It's time silent majority spoke up, says Vinod Rai |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=22 June 2012 |location=Chennai, India |date=14 January 2012}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2016\n| Tamil Ratna\n| America Tamil Sangam\n|<ref>[http://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-news-india/subramanian-swamy-awarded-tamil-ratna-in-united-states/ Subramanian Swamy awarded \u2018Tamil Ratna\u2019 in United States]</ref>\n|}\n\n==Books, research papers and journals==\nSwamy is the author of several books, research papers and journals. A complete list of papers, books and journals authored by him is given below. He has also co-authored with [[Paul Samuelson]], a paper on the Theory of Index Numbers (American Economic Review, 1974) and another in the Royal Economic Society\u2019s Economic Journal (1984).<ref name=\"Swamy Samuelson\"/>\n\n===Books===\n* ''Hindutva and National Renaissance'' (Publisher: Har Anand Publication; {{ISBN|978-81-241-1527-5}})\n* ''Virat Hindu Identity - Concept and its Power'' (Publisher: Har Anand Publication; {{ISBN|978-81-241-1770-5}})\n* ''Economic Growth in China and India, 1952\u201370'' (Publisher: University of Chicago Press; {{ISBN|978-0-226-78315-4}})\n* ''Indian economic planning: An alternative approach'' (Publisher: Barnes & Noble / Vikas publications ; {{ISBN|978-0-389-04202-0}})\n* ''Building a New India: An Agenda for National Renaissance'' (Publisher: UBS PUBLISHERS' AND DISTRIBUTORS LTD; {{ISBN|978-81-85674-21-6}})\n* ''India's Labour Standards and the WTO Framework'' (Publisher: Konark Publishers; {{ISBN|978-81-220-0585-1}})\n* ''India's economic performance and reforms: A perspective for the new millennium'' (Publisher: Konark Publishers; {{ISBN|978-81-220-0594-3}})\n* ''Assassination of Rajiv Gandhi: Unanswered Questions and Unasked Queries'' (Publisher: Konark Publishers; {{ISBN|978-81-220-0591-2}})\n* ''India's China perspective'' (Publisher: Konark Publishers; {{ISBN|978-81-220-0606-3}})\n* ''Financial Architecture and Economic Development in China and India'' (Publisher: Konark Publishers; {{ISBN|978-81-220-0718-3}})\n* ''Trade and Industry in Japan: A Guide to Indian Entrepreneurs and Businessmen'' (Publisher: Prentice-Hall of India; {{ISBN|978-81-203-0785-8}})\n* ''Sri Lanka in Crisis: India's Options'' (Publisher: Har Anand Publications; {{ISBN|978-81-241-1260-1}})\n* ''Kailas and Manasarovar after 22 years in Shiva's domain'' (Publisher: Allied Publishers)\n* ''Hindus Under Siege'' (Publisher: Har Anand Publications; {{ISBN|978-81-241-1207-6}})\n* ''Rama Setu: Symbol of National Unity'' (Publisher: Har Anand Publications; {{ISBN|978-81-241-1418-6}})\n* ''Terrorism in India: A Strategy of Deterrence for India's National Security'' (Publisher: Har Anand Publications; {{ISBN|978-81-241-1344-8}})\n* ''Corruption and Corporate Governance in India: Satyam, Spectrum & Sundaram'' (Publisher: Har Anand Publications; {{ISBN|978-81-241-1486-5}})\n* ''2G Spectrum Scam'' (Publisher: Har Anand Publications; {{ISBN|978-81-241-1638-8}})\n* ''Electronic Voting Machines: Unconstitutional and Tamperable'' (Publisher: Vision Books; {{ISBN|978-81-7094-798-1}})\n* ''Predictions and Meditations'' (Publisher: India International Centre Quarterly 36, no. 3/4 (2009): 202-22. https://www.jstor.org/stable/23006413.\n* ''[https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/38589813-the-ideology-of-india-s-modern-right The Ideology of India\u2019s Modern Right]'' (Publisher: Har Anand Publication; {{ISBN| 978-8124118924}})\n* ''[https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/48070396-reset RESET: Regaining India\u2019s Economic Legacy]'' (Publisher: Rupa Publications; {{ISBN|978-93-5333-651-6}}) RESET was top selling new [[E-book|eBook]] of 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/books-and-literature/ebooks-which-sold-most-this-amish-tripathi-devdutt-pattanaik-year-amazon-6191464/|title=The year that was: eBooks which sold most this year|date=2019-12-31|website=The Indian Express|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-01}}</ref>\n\n===Articles===\n*  \"Can India make it? India's path to sustained growth\" (Publisher: Harvard Asia Pacific review, Volumes 6\u20138 by Harvard University. Dept. of East Asian Languages and Civilizations, 2002)\n*  \"The response to economic challenge: A comparative economic history of China and India\", 1870\u20131952 (Publisher: The Quarterly Journal of Economics, Volume 93 by Harvard University by the MIT Press, 1979)\n\n===Research papers===\n* Economic growth and income distribution in a developing nation (Publisher: Harvard University, 1965)\n* Nuclear policy for India (Publisher: Bharatiya Jana Sangh Publication, 1968)\n* Plan for full employment (Publisher: Bharatiya Jana Sangh, 1970)\n* Theoretical aspects of index numbers (Publisher: Harvard Institute of Economic Research, 1985)\n* Land reforms: an economist's approach (Publisher: Deendayal Research Institute)\n* Samuelson, P., & Swamy, S. (1974). Invariant Economic Index Numbers and Canonical Duality: Survey and Synthesis. The American Economic Review, 64(4), 566-593. https://www.jstor.org/stable/1813311\n* Swamy, Subramanian. \"On Samuelson's Conjecture.\" Indian Economic Review, New Series, 5, no. 2 (1970): 169-75. https://www.jstor.org/stable/23294448\n* Swamy, S. (1965). Consistency of Fisher's Tests. Econometrica, 33(3), 619-623. doi:1. https://www.jstor.org/stable/1911757 doi:1\n* Swamy, S. (1963). Notes on Fractile Graphical Analysis. Econometrica, 31(3), 551-554. doi:1. https://www.jstor.org/stable/1909994 doi:1\n* Swamy, S. (1969). Optimal Allocation of Investment in A Two-sector Model with Foreign Aid. Indian Economic Review, 4(1), new series, 35-44. https://www.jstor.org/stable/23294380\n* Swamy, S. (1969). Systems Analysis of Strategic Defence Needs: A Sequel. Economic and Political Weekly, 4(18), 772-772. https://www.jstor.org/stable/40739578\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n* {{official website|http://swamy39.blogspot.in}}\n*[http://loksabhaph.nic.in/writereaddata/biodata_1_12/2614.htm Official biographical sketch in Parliament of India website]\n{{Bharatiya Janata Party}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Swamy, Subramanian}}\n[[Category:1939 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Bharatiya Janata Party politicians from Tamil Nadu]]\n[[Category:Bharatiya Jana Sangh politicians]]\n[[Category:Janata Party politicians]]\n[[Category:Politicians from Chennai]]\n[[Category:Indian Hindus]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian economists]]\n[[Category:Tamil Nadu politicians]]\n[[Category:6th Lok Sabha members]]\n[[Category:7th Lok Sabha members]]\n[[Category:Hindu College, Delhi alumni]]\n[[Category:Harvard University alumni]]\n[[Category:Indian Institute of Technology Delhi faculty]]\n[[Category:Harvard University faculty]]\n[[Category:English-language writers from India]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian non-fiction writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian non-fiction writers]]\n[[Category:Indian activists]]\n[[Category:Indian anti-communists]]\n[[Category:Lok Sabha members from Maharashtra]]\n[[Category:12th Lok Sabha members]]\n[[Category:Lok Sabha members from Tamil Nadu]]\n[[Category:Members of the Planning Commission of India]]\n[[Category:Anti-corruption activists]]\n[[Category:Law Ministers of India]]\n[[Category:Rajya Sabha members from Uttar Pradesh]]\n[[Category:Far-right politicians in India]]\n[[Category:Anti-corruption activism in India]]\n[[Category:Indian exiles]]\n[[Category:Indian expatriates in the United States]]\n[[Category:Nominated members of the Rajya Sabha]]\n[[Category:Scientists from Chennai]]\n[[Category:Politicians from Mumbai]]\n[[Category:United Nations officials]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=January 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2014}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n<!--NOTE: please do not add the title \"Dr\" to his name: see [[Wikipedia:Manual of Style (biographies)#Academic titles]]-->| office = [[Member of Parliament, Rajya Sabha]]\n| image = Subramanian Swamy.JPG\n| alt = \n| constituency = [[List of nominated members of Rajya Sabha|Nominated]]\n| constituency2 = [[Uttar Pradesh]]\n| party = [[Bharatiya Janata Party]] {{small|(2013\u2013present)}}\n| otherparty = [[Bharatiya Jana Sangh]] {{small|(1974\u20131977)}}<br/>[[Janata Party]] {{small|(1977\u20132013)}}\n| constituency1 = [[Uttar Pradesh]]\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1939|09|15|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Mylapore]], [[Madras Presidency]], [[British India]]<br/>(now in [[Tamil Nadu]], [[India]])\n| spouse = {{marriage|Roxna Swamy|1966}}\n| children = {{Plainlist|\n* Gitanjali Swamy\n* Suhasini Swamy Haidar \n }}\n| alma_mater = [[University of Delhi]] (BA)<br/>[[Indian Statistical Institute]] (MA)<br/>[[Harvard University]] (PhD)\n| occupation = Politician, economist, statistician\n| term_start = 26 April 2016\n| term_start1 = 1988\n| term_end1 = 1994\n| term_start2 = 1974\n| term_end2 = 1976\n| office3 = [[Ministry of Commerce and Industry (India)|Minister of Commerce and Industry]]\n| predecessor3 = \n| primeminister3 = [[Chandra Shekhar]]\n| successor3 = \n| term_start3 = 10 November 1990\n| term_end3 = 21 June 1991\n| office4 = [[Minister of Law and Justice (India)|Minister of Law and Justice]]\n| primeminister4 = [[Chandra Shekhar]]\n| term_start4 = 10 November 1990\n| term_end4 = 21 June 1991\n| predecessor4 = \n| successor4 = \n| office5 = [[Member of Parliament, Lok Sabha]]\n| term_start5 = 1998\n| term_end5 = 1999\n| constituency5 = [[Madurai (Lok Sabha constituency)|Madurai]]\n| predecessor5 = [[A. G. S. Ram Babu]]\n| successor5 = [[P. Mohan]]\n| term_start6 = 1977\n| term_end6 = 1984\n| constituency6 = [[Mumbai North East (Lok Sabha constituency)|Mumbai North East]]\n| predecessor6 = Rajaram Gopal Kulkarni\n| successor6 = [[Gurudas Kamat]]\n| office7 = President, [[Janata Party]]\n| term_start7 = 1990\n| term_end7 = 2013\n| website = [http://swamy39.blogspot.in/ Official Blog]\n}} \n'''Subramanian Swamy''' (born 15 September 1939) is an Indian [[politician]], [[economist]] and [[statistician]] who serves as a [[List of nominated members of the Rajya Sabha|nominated]] [[Member of Parliament, Rajya Sabha|Member of Parliament in Rajya Sabha]], the upper house of the [[Parliament of India|Indian Parliament]]. He is known for his [[Islamophobia|anti-Muslim]] and [[Hindu nationalism|Hindu nationalist]] views.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|last=Anand|first=Geeta|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/07/02/world/asia/india-subramanian-swamy.html|title=Taking Down Politicians for Decades, and Rising in India\u2019s Government|date=2016-07-01|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-04-02|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.insidehighered.com/news/2011/12/08/harvard-kills-courses-controversial-summer-school-instructor|title=Harvard kills courses by controversial summer school instructor|website=www.insidehighered.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref name = \"removal\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/national/archive/2011/07/harvard-instructor-faces-removal-over-anti-muslim-op-ed/353487/|title=Harvard Instructor May Face Removal Over Anti-Muslim Op-Ed|last=Sehgal|first=Ujala|date=2011-07-30|website=The Atlantic|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> Swamy was a member of the [[Planning Commission (India)|Planning Commission of India]] and was a [[Union Council of Ministers|Cabinet Minister]] in the [[Chandra Shekhar]] government. Between 1994 and 1996, Swamy was Chairman of the Commission on Labour Standards and International Trade under [[List of Prime Ministers of India|former Prime Minister]] [[P. V. Narasimha Rao]].\n\nHe has written on foreign affairs of [[India]] dealing largely with [[China]], [[Pakistan]] and [[Israel]]. He was [[List of nominated members of Rajya Sabha|nominated]] to [[Rajya Sabha]] on 26 April 2016.\n\n==Early life and education==\nSubramanian Swamy was born in [[Mylapore]], [[Chennai]], [[Tamil Nadu]], India, to a family which hailed originally from [[Madurai]] in [[Tamil Nadu]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/analysis/column-the-paradox-called-subramanian-swamy-1567157 |title=The paradox called Subramanian Swamy |date=19 July 2011 |work=dna}}</ref><ref>[http://www.ibtl.in/news/exclusive/1221/subramanian/ Subramanian Swamy : Lets salute the real fighter 'SINGHAM]</ref> His father, Sitarama Subramanian, was a bureaucrat and his mother, Padmavathi, was a homemaker. He has one younger brother, Ram Subramanian as well as two younger sisters.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.firstpost.com/politics/subramanian-swamy-uncovered-doting-wife-leftist-brother-and-more-212638.html |title=Subramanian Swamy uncovered: Doting wife, leftist brother and more |work=Firstpost}}</ref>\n\nSitaraman Subramanian was an [[Civil Services of India|officer]] in the [[Indian Statistical Service]] who served as the director of the [[Central Statistical Organisation|Central Statistical Institute]] in [[Delhi]], and was a statistical adviser to the [[Government of India]].<ref name=\"Subramanian Swamy - Tehelka\"/> The family, which hailed from [[Madurai]] in [[Tamil Nadu]], moved to [[New Delhi]] when Swamy was only six months old. Due to his father's job and the family's [[Tamil language|Tamil]] roots, major national leaders like [[K. Kamaraj]], [[C. Rajagopalachari]] and [[S. Satyamurti]] often visited Sitaraman.<ref name=\"Swamy - Solution or Riddle\">{{cite web |title=The Jury Is Out, Subramanian Swamy: is the man a solution o\\r a riddle? |url=http://www.outlookindia.com/magazine/story/the-jury-is-out/279890 |work=[[Outlook (Indian magazine)|Outlook]] |accessdate=3 January 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"Swamy inscrutable\">{{cite web |title=The Outlier: The inscrutable politics of Subramanian Swamy |url=http://caravanmagazine.in/Story.aspx?Storyid=1389&StoryStyle=FullStory |work=[[The Caravan]] |accessdate=5 May 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120504172103/http://caravanmagazine.in/Story.aspx?Storyid=1389&StoryStyle=FullStory |archivedate=4 May 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"swamy queries\">{{cite web |title=Subramanian Swamy: Queries and Answers, Interview |url=http://www.rediff.com/news/report/why-should-i-dislike-chidambaram-subramanian-swamy/20120102.htm |accessdate=3 January 2012}}</ref>\n\nSwamy attended [[Hindu College, University of Delhi]], from where he earned his bachelor's degree in Mathematics. He then took his master's degree in Statistics from the [[Indian Statistical Institute]], [[Kolkata]]. He was later recommended by [[Hendrik S. Houthakker]]<ref name=\"Swamy inscrutable\"/> and went to study at [[Harvard University]] on a full [[Rockefeller]] scholarship,<ref name=\"Swamy inscrutable\"/> where he received his PhD in Economics in 1965, with his thesis titled ''Economic Growth and Income Distribution in a Developing Nation''.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.genealogy.math.ndsu.nodak.edu/id.php?id=208481 |title = Subramanian Swamy - the Mathematics Genealogy Project}}</ref> His thesis adviser was [[Nobel laureate]] [[Simon Kuznets]].<ref name=\"Swamy inscrutable\"/><ref name=\"Guru PhD: Swamy\">{{cite web |title=An Indian tribute: Paul Samuelson, Guru |url=http://business.rediff.com/special/2009/dec/17/subramanian-swamy-pays-tribute-to-paul-samuelson.htm |accessdate=29 December 2011}}</ref> While he was a doctoral student at Harvard, he attended [[Massachusetts Institute of Technology]] as a cross-registered student<ref name=\"Swamy Samuelson\">{{cite news |url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/opinion/subramanian-swamy-samuelson-a-genius-who-was-my-guru-109122200056_1.html |title=Subramanian Swamy: Samuelson - A genius who was my guru|publisher=[[Business Standard]]|newspaper=Business Standard India|date=22 December 2009|last1=Swamy|first1=Subramanian}}</ref> and later worked at the [[United Nations Secretariat]] in [[New York City]] as an Assistant Economics Affairs Officer in 1963. He subsequently worked as a resident tutor at [[Lowell House]] at Harvard University.<ref name=\"Harvard economist enemity\">{{cite web |title=Harvard Economist Accused of 'Spreading Enmity Between Communities' |url=https://www.thecrimson.com/flyby/article/2011/10/5/indian-india-swamy-current/ |publisher=[[Harvard Crimson]], Flyby The blog of The Harvard Crimson|accessdate=14 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Academic career==\nIn July 1965, immediately after obtaining his PhD in economics from [[Harvard]], Swamy joined the Department of Economics at the [[Harvard Faculty of Arts and Sciences]] as an assistant professor.<ref name=\"Swamy inscrutable\"/><ref name=\"Swamy recovery IITD\">{{cite web |url=http://zeenews.india.com/news/nation/hc-swamy-s-plea-for-recovery-of-dues-from-iit_760640.html |title=High Court of Delhi : Swamy's plea for recovery of dues from IIT |publisher=[[Zee News]] |accessdate=27 February 2012}}</ref> In 1969, he was made an associate professor.<ref name=\"Harvard removes Subramanian Swamy's courses over controversial column\">{{cite web |url=http://www.indiaeducationreview.com/news/harvard-removes-subramanian-swamys-courses-over-controversial-column |title=Harvard removes Subramanian Swamy's courses over controversial column |publisher=Indiaeducationreview}}</ref> As associate professor, he was invited by [[Amartya Sen]]<ref name=\"Subramanian Swamy - Tehelka\">{{cite web |url=http://archive.tehelka.com/story_main51.asp?filename=Ne311211Coverstory.asp |title=The Beastly Beatitudes: The rise, fall and resurrection of Subramanian Swamy}}</ref> to occupy the chair on Chinese studies at the [[Delhi School of Economics]].<ref name=\"Swamy - Solution or Riddle\"/> He accepted the offer and even travelled to India to take up the position, but his appointment was cancelled at the last minute due to his views on India's economic policy and also its nuclear policy.<ref name=\"Subramanian Swamy - Tehelka\"/> At that time, [[Socialism in India|India was still partially oriented towards socialism]] and the \"command economy\" model instituted by [[Nehru]], and Swamy was a believer in market economy.\n\nThereafter, Swamy moved to the [[Indian Institute of Technology, Delhi]] and he was a full Professor of Mathematical Economics there from 1969 to the early 1970s.<ref name=\"Swamy recovery IITD\"/><ref name=\"Swamy Rediff\">{{cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/news/1998/mar/17sswamy.htm |title=The Rediff Special: The Man People Love to Hate |publisher=[[Rediff.com]]}}</ref> He was removed from the position by its board of governors in the early 1970s but was legally reinstated in the late 1990s by the [[Supreme Court of India]]. He continued in the position until 1991 when he resigned to become a cabinet minister. He served on the Board of Governors of the IIT, Delhi (1977\u201380) and on the Council of IITs (1980\u201382). He also taught economics courses at [[Harvard Summer School]]<ref>{{cite news |author=Special Correspondent |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/article1455140.ece |title=Swamy to teach at Harvard |location=Chennai |work=The Hindu |date=15 February 2011}}</ref> until 2011, when the Harvard faculty voted to eliminate Swamy's courses as a result of his \"offensive\" statements about Muslims.<ref name=\":1\"/><ref name = \"removal\"/>\n\nSwamy now serves as Chairman of the [[School of Communication and Management Studies]] in [[Kochi]].<ref name=SCMSMgmt>{{cite web |title=Management |url=http://scmsgroup.org/php/showContent.php?linkid=295&partid=2 |work=SCMS Group of Institutions |publisher=SCMS Group}}</ref><ref name=In.com>{{cite web |title=Politician Subramanian Swamy |url=http://www.in.com/subramanian-swamy/profile-262171.html |work=In.com India |publisher=In.com (web18)}}</ref>\n\n==Political career==\n\n===Early politics===\nSwamy's career started with his involvement in the Sarvodaya movement, which was an apolitical movement but which formed the foundation of the creation of [[Janata Party]] later.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://janataparty.org/articledetail.asp?rowid=8 |title=My Experiences with Jayaprakash Narayan&nbsp;\u2014 Subramanian Swamy |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120828044859/http://janataparty.org/articledetail.asp?rowid=8 |archivedate=28 August 2012 |publisher=Janata Party Website}}</ref> The real turn in his political career came after his sacking from IIT. Liberal economic policies put forward by him did not go well with the then Prime Minister [[Indira Gandhi]] who sneered at his plans as 'Santa Claus with unrealistic ideas'. He was later expelled from [[Indian Institute of Technology]]. This marked the beginning of his active political career. Staunch opponent of Indira Gandhi [[Bharatiya Jana Sangh]] sent him to [[Rajya Sabha]] \u2013 the upper house of Indian Parliament.<ref name=\"Subramanian Swamy - Tehelka\"/>\n\nHe was elected Member of Parliament 5 times between 1974 and 1999. He has twice represented the city of Mumbai North East during 1977 and 1980, Uttar Pradesh and Tamil Nadu in the Parliament.<ref name=\"Subramanian Swamy - Tehelka\"/>\n\nDuring the period of the [[Indian Emergency|Emergency]], he fled to the United States, seeking haven with an Indian businessman in [[Michigan]] who had become the spokesperson of the opposition in the United States. In 1976, when the Emergency was still in force and an arrest warrant had been issued in his name, Swamy came to Parliament to attend the session and managed to escape India after the session was adjourned. This act of defiance was well received in the eyes of opposition parties.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sunday-guardian.com/investigation/animosity-between-pc-swamy-spans-decades |title=Animosity between PC, Swamy spans decades |publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://newindianexpress.com/states/tamil_nadu/Cables-Swamy-an-ultranationalist/2013/04/13/article1542610.ece |title=Cables: Swamy, an ultranationalist |work=The New Indian Express}}</ref>\n\nSwamy was one of the founding members of the [[Janata Party]] and served as its president till 2013.\n\n===Electoral history ===\n1974\u201376 - Member of [[Rajya Sabha]] from [[Uttar Pradesh]], elected on a [[Jan Sangh]] party ticket <br/>\n1977-80 - Member of [[Lok Sabha]] from [[Mumbai North East (Lok Sabha constituency)|Mumbai North-East]], elected on a [[Janata Party]] ticket <br/>\n1980-84 - Member of [[Lok Sabha]] from [[Mumbai North East (Lok Sabha constituency)|Mumbai North-East]], elected on a [[Janata Party]] ticket <br/>\n1988\u201394 - Member of [[Rajya Sabha]] from [[Uttar Pradesh]], elected on a [[Janata Party]] ticket <br/>\n1998-99 - Member of [[Lok Sabha]] from [[Madurai (Lok Sabha constituency)|Madurai]], elected on a [[Janata Party]] ticket <br/>\n2016 - Member of [[Rajya Sabha]], [[List of nominated members of Rajya Sabha|Nominated Category]]\n\n===Minister of Commerce and Law of India===\nDuring 1990 and 1991, Swamy served as a member of the [[Planning Commission (India)|Planning Commission of India]] and as Cabinet Minister of Commerce and Law. Albeit uncorroborated, During this period, Swamy claims to have provided the blueprint for the [[Economic liberalisation in India|economic reforms in India]] under Prime Minister [[Chandra Shekhar]]<ref name=\"Wither India Reform\">{{cite news |title=Whither economic reforms? India |url=http://www.frontline.in/static/html/fl1719/17190780.htm |publisher=[[Frontline (magazine)|Frontline, The Hindu]] |accessdate=7 January 2012 |location=Chennai, India}}</ref><ref name=\"Swamy India Reform\"/> which was later carried out in 1991 by [[Manmohan Singh]],<ref name=\"Swamy inscrutable\"/> then Finance Minister under leadership of Prime Minister [[Narasimha Rao]].<ref name=\"Swamy India Reform\">{{cite web |title=Assessing India's economic reforms: Swamy |url=http://www.frontlineonnet.com/fl1902/19020610.htm |publisher=Frontline, The Hindu |accessdate=12 October 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111127052246/http://www.frontlineonnet.com/fl1902/19020610.htm |archivedate=27 November 2011}}</ref> In the Narasimha Rao government, Swamy was Chairman of the Commission on Labour Standards and International Trade, which was a Cabinet-rank post.<ref>http://www.dnaindia.com/india/report-subramanian-swamy-demands-bharat-ratna-for-p-v-narasimha-rao-2046472</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/why-subramanian-swamy-should-determine-whether-to-be-an-asset-or-liability-for-modi-government/articleshow/53023135.cms |title = Why Subramanian Swamy should determine whether to be an asset or liability for Modi government|newspaper = The Economic Times|date = 3 July 2016|last1 = Mukhopadhyay|first1 = Nilanjan}}</ref>  In his book, Swamy asserts that Manmohan Singh acknowledges his role as well.<ref name=\"Swamy - SCMS Group Chair\">{{cite web |url=http://scmsgroup.org/php/showContent.php?linkid=295&partid=2 |title=Board of Management of the SCMS Group of Educational Institutions: Chairman Subramanian Swamy}}</ref><ref name=\"shfe\">{{cite book |title=Financial Architecture and Economic Development in China and India |publisher=Konark Publishers Pvt Ltd |isbn=978-81-220-0718-3}}</ref>\n\n===Later years===\n[[File:The book \"Moditva \u2013 the Idea behind the Man\" being launched by Rajnath Singh.jpg|thumb|250px|right|Swamy at launching a book with BJP members in 2014.]]\nBetween 1994 and 1996, Swamy was chairman of the Commission on Labour Standards and International Trade (equivalent in rank to a cabinet minister) under Prime Minister [[P. V. Narasimha Rao]].<ref name=\"Subramanian Swamy - Tehelka\"/> He continued to be president of the Janata Party till 2013. On 11 August 2013, Swamy officially joined [[Bharatiya Janata Party|BJP]] when its president was Rajnath Singh. His admission to the party would mark the merger of the Janata Party with the Bharatiya Janata Party.<ref name=\"indianexpress1\">{{cite web |url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/subramanian-swamys-janta-party-merges-with-bjp/1153983/?socialmedia |title=Subramanian Swamy's Janta Party merges with BJP |work=The Indian Express |date=11 August 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Court petitions==\n\n===Petition to strike down anti-defamation laws===\nIn Oct 2014, Swamy filed a petition in Supreme Court praying for declaring Sections 499 and 500 of the Indian Penal Code that deal with criminal defamation  as unconstitutional.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://supremecourtofindia.nic.in/outtoday/wr18414p-2014_10_30.pdf |title=SUPREME COURT OF INDIA RECORD OF PROCEEDINGS |work=Su |publisher=Supreme Court of India |accessdate=2016-01-18 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160507144638/http://supremecourtofindia.nic.in/outtoday/wr18414p-2014_10_30.pdf |archivedate=7 May 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n===Complaint against Jayalalithaa===\nIn 1996, Swamy had filed a criminal complaint against [[Jayalalithaa]] which led to [[Disproportionate Asset case against Jayalalithaa|her prosecution]], conviction and sentencing to four years imprisonment by the trial court in 2014.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/live-jayalalithaa-wealth-case-verdict/article6452086.ece |title=Jayalalithaa conviction: As it happened |newspaper=The Hindu |access-date=2017-02-19 |language=en}}</ref> Later, on May 11, 2015, a special Bench of the [[Karnataka High Court]] set aside the trial court order convicting former Tamil Nadu Chief Minister Jayalalitha, who was acquitted of all charges in the disproportionate assets case.<ref>{{cite news |title=Dr. Subramanian Swamy vs J. Jayalalitha on 20 August 1996 |url=http://indiankanoon.org/doc/1137705/}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Jayalalithaa guilty in assets case, Gets 4-year jail term |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/jayalalithaa-verdict-assets-case-disproportionate-special-court/1/393035.html |publisher=India Today |date=27 September 2014 |location=Bangalore |accessdate=27 September 2014}}</ref> An Appeal against the High court verdict was filed in Supreme Court.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.ndtv.com/tamil-nadu-news/supreme-court-to-hear-karnatakas-plea-against-jayalalithaas-acquittal-1231332 |title=Supreme Court to Hear Karnataka's Plea Against Jayalalithaa's Acquittal |work=NDTV |date=2015-10-12 |accessdate=2016-01-18}}</ref> However, keeping personal differences aside, he wished her a speedy recovery on her recent illness and advised she visit [[Singapore]] for treatment.<ref>{{cite tweet |user=Swamy39 |author=Subramanian Swamy |number=779332399838572544 |date=23 September 2016 |title=JJ should take my advice to charter a plane and go to Singapore for medical attention. We may be opponents but wish her long life and health}}</ref> The final verdict of Supreme Court came in February, 2017 that indicted [[Jayalalithaa|Jayalalitha]] posthumously and upheld the trial court judgement [[wikt:in toto|in toto]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/Jayalalithaa-Sasikala-criminally-conspired-at-Poes-Garden-to-launder-ill-gotten-wealth-SC/article17301596.ece |title=Jayalalithaa, Sasikala criminally conspired at Poes Garden to launder ill-gotten wealth: SC |last=Rajagopal |first=Krishnadas |newspaper=The Hindu |access-date=2017-02-19 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n===Phone tapping allegation===\n\nSwamy released a letter alleging that former intelligence chief had asked [[Department of Telecommunications|DoT]] to [[Phone tapping|tap the phone]] of many politicians and businessmen in [[Karnataka]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Watch-out-Your-phone-may-be-tapped/articleshow/1190723.cms?referral=PM |title=Watch out! Your phone may be tapped |work=The Times of India}}</ref> when [[Ramakrishna Hegde]], the then Chief Minister, resigned in 1988.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Repository/getFiles.asp?Style=OliveXLib:LowLevelEntityToPrint_TOINEW&Type=text/html&Locale=english-skin-custom&Path=TOIBG/2010/04/26&ID=Ar01501 |title=Phone-tapping allegations forced Hegde to quit in '88 |publisher=}}</ref> Hegde then filed a case against him in 1989 and 1990.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://indiankanoon.org/doc/1559770/ |title=Dr. Subramaniam Swamy vs Ramakrishna Hegde on 18 October, 1989 |publisher=}}</ref><ref>[http://judis.nic.in/supremecourt/imgs1.aspx?filename=39307] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131219001856/http://judis.nic.in/supremecourt/imgs1.aspx?filename=39307|date=19 December 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://supremecourtofindia.nic.in/scr/2012_v5_piv.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-12-18 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130818204917/http://supremecourtofindia.nic.in/scr/2012_v5_piv.pdf |archivedate=18 August 2013 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n===Hashimpura massacre===\n{{Main|Hashimpura massacre}}\nIn 1987, when Muslim youths were killed under police custody, Swamy spoke against it and sat on a fast for more than a week in Jantar Mantar demanding the institution of an inquiry.<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.dailypioneer.com/columnists/item/51993-why-is-bjp-always-doing-congress-a-favour?.html |title=Why is BJP always doing Congress a favour? |periodical=[[The Pioneer (Indian newspaper)|Daily Pioneer]] |date=14 July 2012 |author=Shahroze Tariq Raza |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120716233544/http://www.dailypioneer.com/columnists/item/51993-why-is-bjp-always-doing-congress-a-favour?.html |archivedate=16 July 2012}}</ref> After 25 years he started pursuing the case once again in court.<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.oneindia.com/2012/07/10/subramanian-swamy-gets-weapon-against-chidambaram-riot-1032579.html |title=Subramanian Swamy gets brahmastra against Chidambaram |periodical=[[Oneindia.in|News One India]] |date=10 July 2012}}</ref>\n\nRebecca John, a counsel for the Hashimpura complainants, told Additional Sessions Judge Rakesh Siddhartha who is conducting the trial in the case, that \"there is no other motive than politics behind Swamy's plea for further investigation and it would only further delay the trial\".<ref>{{cite web |author=TNN |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-01-08/india/36215347_1_hashimpura-subramanian-swamy-janata-party-president |title=Hashimpura massacre case: Victims oppose Subramanian Swamy's plea for further probe |work=The Times of India |date=8 January 2013 |access-date=19 January 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130119181437/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-01-08/india/36215347_1_hashimpura-subramanian-swamy-janata-party-president |archive-date=19 January 2013 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n===Role in exposing 2G spectrum case===\n{{main|2G spectrum case}}\nIn November 2008, Swamy amongst others wrote the first of five letters to Prime Minister [[Manmohan Singh]] seeking permission to prosecute [[A. Raja]] in regard to [[2G spectrum case]].<ref>{{cite news |title=2G chronology |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/India-news/NewDelhi/Chronology-of-events-in-the-2G-scam-case/Article1-805604.aspx |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120824100351/http://www.hindustantimes.com/India-news/NewDelhi/Chronology-of-events-in-the-2G-scam-case/Article1-805604.aspx |archivedate=24 August 2012}}</ref> After not receiving any response,<ref name=\"spectrum corruption\">{{cite web |title=2G Spectrum Shadiness |url=http://www.caravanmagazine.in/Story/615/Spectrum-Shadiness.html |work=[[The Caravan]] |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101130091658/http://caravanmagazine.in/Story/615/Spectrum-Shadiness.html |archivedate=30 November 2010 |accessdate=5 May 2012}}</ref> Swamy decided to file a case on his own in the [[Supreme Court of India]] regarding the matter, which then asked the [[Central Bureau of Investigation]] to produce a detailed report on it.<ref>{{citation |periodical=The Hindu |date=6 February 2011 |accessdate=1 August 2011 |url=http://www.hindu.com/2011/02/06/stories/2011020659910600.htm |title=CBI asked to file detailed report on 2G scam |author=Jiby Kattakayam |location=Chennai, India |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110825071135/http://www.hindu.com/2011/02/06/stories/2011020659910600.htm |archivedate=25 August 2011 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> He further called on the Indian government to re-auction the [[2G]] spectrum without the involvement of Communications Minister [[Kapil Sibal]].<ref>{{citation |url=http://in.news.yahoo.com/auction-2g-spectrum-restrain-sibal-subramanian-swamy-20110110-034015-410.html |title=Re-auction 2G spectrum, restrain Sibal: Subramanian Swamy |agency=[[Indo-Asian News Service]] |date=11 January 2011 |accessdate=1 August 2011}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 April 2011, he filed a 206-page petition with PM Singh seeking permission to prosecute [[Sonia Gandhi]] on charges of corruption. He also raised doubts regarding her acquisition of Indian citizenship.<ref>{{citation |url=http://newindianexpress.com/states/tamil_nadu/article383222.ece |periodical=The New Indian Express |title=Permit me to prosecute Sonia: Swamy |date=19 April 2011 |accessdate=1 August 2011}}</ref> Swamy filed documents in the court to prosecute [[Minister for Home Affairs (India)|Minister of Home Affairs]] [[P. Chidambaram]] by including a 15 January 2008 letter written by Chidambaram to Prime Minister Manmohan Singh. Swamy also placed on record the certified copy of the minutes of a meeting between Chidambaram, Raja and the prime minister during the tenure of Raja as the MOC&IT.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics/nation/2g-case-subramanian-swamy-submits-documents-against-chidambaram-arguments-on-january-21/articleshow/11399259.cms |title=2G case: Subramanian Swamy submits documents against Chidambaram, arguments on January 21 |work=The Economic Times |date=7 January 2012 |accessdate=7 January 2012}}</ref> Since criminal charges were filed against the accused, but no evidence was given by Swamy or the CBI, all the respondents have got bail as of July 2012.\n\n====Sanction to prosecute telecom minister A. Raja====\nOn 31 January 2012, the [[Supreme Court of India]] accepted Swamy's petition against the [[Prime Minister's Office (India)|Prime Minister's Office]] in the 2G case, saying that all public authorities should give a sanction within three months against any public official if a request is made for prosecution.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/2g-case-sc-allows-swamys-petition-on-grant-of-sanction/articleshow/11696767.cms|title=2G case: SC allows Swamy's petition on grant of sanction|date=2012-01-31|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2020-01-01}}</ref>\n\nThe Supreme Court said that Swamy had the [[locus standi]] to seek sanction from the Prime Minister for the prosecution of [[A Raja]] in the 2G case. Sanction by a competent authority for the prosecution of a public servant has to be granted within a time frame, the apex court said. Justice [[AK Ganguly]] said that the sanction would be deemed to be granted if competent authority failed to take a decision within four months.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Prosecuting-corrupt-officials-SC-sets-deadline-for-govt/articleshow/11696857.cms|title=Prosecuting corrupt officials: SC sets deadline for govt {{!}} India News - Times of India|last=Jan 31|first=PTI {{!}} Updated|last2=2012|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2020-01-01|last3=Ist|first3=12:08}}</ref>\n\nSwamy's arguments were that he wrote to the PMO on 29 November 2008, but it was only on 19 March 2010 the PMO replied that the plea made by Swamy was \"premature\" as investigation was being carried out by the [[Central Bureau of Investigation]] (CBI).\nRaja was arrested by the CBI in the case and got bail on 15 May 2012 after spending nearly 15 months in the [[Tihar Jail|Tihar Central Jail]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/article3421102.ece |location=Chennai |work=The Hindu |title=Raja gets bail, walks out of Tihar jail |date=15 May 2012}}</ref>\n\nOn December 21, 2017, the special CBI Court Judge acquitted the accused including [[Andimuthu Raja]].<ref>[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/2g-scam-verdict-today/liveblog/62187750.cms 2G scam case: All accused acquitted]</ref>\n\n=== Petition to strike down \"single directive provision\" ===\nIn 1997, Swamy filed a petition in the [[Supreme Court of India]] to strike down a provision which barred [[Central Bureau of Investigation|CBI]] from investigating corruption charges against officers of the rank of joint secretary and above without prior permission of the [[Govt of India]] called as ''\"Dr. Subramanian Swamy Versus Director, Central Bureau of Investigation & Anr.\"''<ref name=\"With govt's single directive, law no longer above all\">{{cite news |title=With govt's single directive, law no longer above all |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/With-govts-single-directive-law-no-longer-above-all/articleshow/1019946.cms |accessdate=6 May 2014}}</ref> On 6 May 2014, a five-judge [[Constitution Bench (India)|constitution bench]] held the single directive provision as invalid and unconstitutional. The court said that \"Protection of prior approval for probing graft charges against officers at level of joint secretary and above has propensity of shielding corruption\"<ref>{{cite news |title=CBI can investigate corruption charges against top babus without govt nod: SC |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/CBI-can-investigate-corruption-charges-against-top-babus-without-govt-nod-SC/articleshow/34726114.cms |accessdate=6 May 2014 |date=6 May 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"Supreme Court Judgement in WRIT PETITION (CIVIL) NO. 38 OF 1997\">{{cite web |title=Supreme Court Judgement in WRIT PETITION (CIVIL) NO. 38 OF 1997 |url=http://sci.nic.in/outtoday/41503.pdf |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140506183826/http://sci.nic.in/outtoday/41503.pdf |archivedate=2014-05-06}}</ref> Experts such as former CBI Director Joginder Singh praised the judgement as \"Superb\".<ref name=\"Experts hail Supreme Court's decision\">{{cite news |title=Experts hail Supreme Court's decision |url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ani/experts-hail-supreme-court-s-decision-on-investigating-officers-of-jt-secretary-rank-114050601408_1.html |accessdate=6 May 2014}}</ref> Incumbent CBI Director [[Ranjit Sinha]] welcomed the judgement and said, \"now a very heavy responsibility has been cast upon us to ensure that no innocent civil-servant is harassed.\"<ref name=\"CBI welcomes Supreme Court decision\">{{cite news |title=CBI welcomes Supreme Court decision |url=http://www.aninews.in/newsdetail2/story167291/cbi-welcomes-supreme-court-decision-on-investigating-officers-of-jt-secretary-rank.html |accessdate=6 May 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140511030532/http://www.aninews.in/newsdetail2/story167291/cbi-welcomes-supreme-court-decision-on-investigating-officers-of-jt-secretary-rank.html |archivedate=11 May 2014 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n===Investigation on EVM===\n{{further|Indian voting machines}}\n\nSwamy demanded that an independent committee should be formed to check the security and safety of the [[Indian voting machines|Electronic Voting Machines]] (EVM) to avoid any rigging or tampering. He demanded that a printed receipt should be given to every voter after casting the vote.<ref>{{cite news |author=Special Correspondent |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/swamy-for-expert-panel-on-secure-evms/article106271.ece |title=Swamy for expert panel on secure EVMs |location=CHENNAI |work=The Hindu |date=13 February 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/evms-not-tamperfree/article712729.ece |title=EVMs not tamper-free |newspaper=The Hindu |date=18 February 2010}}</ref> His [[Public-interest litigation (India)|PIL]] to investigate the working of EVM was dismissed by the [[Delhi High Court]] on 17 January 2012. The court refused to give any direction to the [[Election Commission of India|Election Commission]] to bring back paper-ballot system or use of printed receipts. The Commission argued that the use of paper is not feasible due to the huge size of Indian electorate. The court further asked the Election Commission to \"immediately begin a process of wider consultations\" and the Parliament \"to go into this question in depth and decide\".<ref>{{cite web |author=Anita |url=http://www.oneindia.com/2012/01/17/delhi-hc-says-not-impossible-to-tamper-evm-s.html |title=Delhi High Court says not impossible to tamper EVMs |publisher=OneIndia |date=17 January 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/delhi-hc-rejects-swamys-plea-to-bring-back-paper-ballots/900646 |title=Delhi HC rejects Swamy's plea to bring back paper ballots |work=The Indian Express |date=17 January 2012}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 January 2013 the [[Election Commission of India|Election Commission]] informed the [[Supreme Court of India|Supreme Court]] that it would include [[Voter-verified paper audit trail|Voter Verifiable Paper Audit Trail]] (VVPAT) system which is in the testing phase after the court agreed with some points raised by Swamy who was the contender,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://supremecourtofindia.nic.in/outtoday/9093.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-10-10 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303231056/http://supremecourtofindia.nic.in/outtoday/9093.pdf |archivedate=3 March 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> in the machines so that every voter will come to know who he/she is voting by getting a printed slip after pressing the EVM button.<ref>{{cite web |author=PTI |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Voter-to-get-paper-receipt-after-casting-ballot-EC-tells-SC/articleshow/18134882.cms?referral=PM |title=Voter to get paper receipt after casting ballot: EC tells SC |work=The Times of India |date=22 January 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=Legal Correspondent |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/voter-paper-trail-in-phases-ec/article4333597.ece |title=Voter paper trail in phases: EC |newspaper=The Hindu |date=23 January 2013}}</ref> The voter paper audit trail has then been in use from 4 September 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.jagranjosh.com/current-affairs/ec-to-use-voter-verifiable-paper-audit-trail-vvpat-system-in-nagaland-bypolls-1376729528-1 |title=EC to use Voter Verifiable Paper Audit Trail (VVPAT) System in Nagaland by-polls |work=Jagranjosh.com|date=17 August 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-newdelhi/new-delhi-voters-can-verify-who-they-voted-for/article5362745.ece |title=New Delhi voters can verify who they voted for |newspaper=The Hindu|date=18 November 2013 }}</ref>\n\nOn 8 October 2013 the Supreme Court directed the Election Commission to implement audit trail system in [[2014 Indian general election|2014 general election]] in phases.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.jagranjosh.com/current-affairs/supreme-court-1381300734-1 |title=Supreme Court Directed Election Commission to Install VVPAT System in EVMs for 2014 Polls |work=Jagranjosh.com|date=9 October 2013 }}</ref>\n\n===National Herald case ===\n{{Main|National Herald Case}}\nOn 1 November 2012 Swamy alleged that both [[Sonia Gandhi|Sonia]] and [[Rahul Gandhi]] have committed fraud and [[land grabbing]] to a tune of {{INRConvert|20|b}} by acquiring a public ltd company called Associated Journals Private Ltd (AJPL) through their owned private company, Young Indian<ref>{{cite web |url=http://indianexpress.com/article/explained/national-herald-case-where-the-matter-stands/ |title=National Herald case explained: Everything that you need to know |publisher=[[The Indian Express]] |date=8 December 2015}}</ref> which was formed on 23 November 2010.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/congress-to-revive-national-herald-challenges-swamy-to-take-it-to-court/article4058571.ece |title=Congress to revive National Herald, challenges Swamy to take it to court |newspaper=[[The Hindu]] |date=3 November 2015|last1=Gupta |first1=Smita }}</ref> Through this they had got publication rights of ''[[The National Herald (India)|National Herald]]'' and ''[[Qaumi Awaz]]'' newspapers, with real estate properties in Delhi and Uttar Pradesh.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/national-herald-case-enforcement-directorate-mulling-probe-possibility/article7959871.ece |title=National Herald case: Enforcement Directorate mulling probe possibility |newspaper=[[The Hindu]] |date=8 December 2015|last1=Pandey |first1=Devesh K. }}</ref> The acquired place was intended only for newspaper purposes but were used for running a passport office, amounting to [[Crore|crores]] of rupees, it alleges.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/wealth/personal-finance-news/national-herald-case-heres-how-much-associated-journals-seven-properties-worth/articleshow/50165303.cms|title=National Herald case: Here's how much Associated Journals' seven properties worth|last=Babar|first=Kailash|date=2015-12-14|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2020-01-01|last2=Sharma|first2=Ravi Teja}}</ref> Swamy further added that Rahul Gandhi hid the facts in his affidavit while filing nomination for the [[2009 Indian general election|2009 Lok Sabha elections]].<ref>{{cite web |author=Sanjay Singh |url=http://www.firstpost.com/politics/swamy-does-a-kejriwal-targets-sonia-rahul-for-landgrab-511644.html |title=Swamy does a Kejriwal, targets Sonia & Rahul for landgrab |publisher=Firstpost |date=1 November 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=New Delhi, 1 Nov 2012, DHNS |url=http://www.deccanherald.com/content/289449/swamy-accuses-sonia-rahul-property.html |title=Swamy accuses Sonia, Rahul of property fraud |work=Deccan Herald |date=1 November 2012}}</ref>\n\nIt further alleges that on 26 February 2011 AJPL approved the transfer of [[Unsecured debt|unsecured loan]] of {{INRConvert|900|m}} from the [[All India Congress Committee]] at zero interest.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/rahul-threatens-to-sue-subramanian-swamy/article4055087.ece |title=Rahul threatens to sue Subramanian Swamy |newspaper=[[The Hindu]] |date=2 November 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indiatoday.in/story/national-herald-case-sonia-gandhi-rahul-will-have-to-appear-in-court/1/540297.html |title=National Herald case: Sonia Gandhi, Rahul will have to appear in court |publisher=[[India Today]] |date=7 December 2015}}{{dead link|date=May 2016|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref> Swamy argued that it is illegal for any political party to lend the loan as per violation of Section 269T of Income Tax Act 1961.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/what-is-the-national-herald-case-all-about/1/541733.html |title=What is the National Herald case all about? |publisher=[[India Today]] |date=8 December 2015}}</ref> On 2 November, the party responded that the loan was given only for reviving National Herald newspaper with no commercial interest.<ref>{{cite news |author=Smita Gupta |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/congress-to-revive-national-herald-challenges-swamy-to-take-it-to-court/article4058571.ece |title=Congress to revive National Herald, challenges Swamy to take it to court |newspaper=The Hindu |date=2 November 2012}}</ref> Swamy decided to approach the Supreme Court for de-recognising the Congress party, while the Election Commission ordered the probe on 17 November 2012.<ref>{{cite news |agency=Press Trust of India |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/swamy-to-move-court-against-ec/article4073917.ece |title=Swamy to move court against EC |work=The Hindu |date=7 November 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.news18.com/news/politics/ec-orders-probe-against-rahul-gandhi-for-wrong-information-522167.html |title=EC orders probe against Rahul Gandhi for 'wrong information' about his assets- Politics News- Politics-IBNLive |publisher=Ibnlive.in.com |date=17 November 2012}}</ref>\n\nThe hearing of the case had been taken up thereafter on different occasions<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.oneindia.com/2013/03/16/subramanian-swamy-s-victory-against-sonia-rahul-gandhi-1173225.html |title=Subramanian Swamy's victory against Sonia, Rahul Gandhi |publisher=One India |date=16 March 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dailypioneer.com/nation/national-herald-acquisition-delhi-court-summons-roc-to-testify-records.html |title=NATIONAL HERALD ACQUISITION: DELHI COURT SUMMONS ROC TO TESTIFY RECORDS |publisher=dailypioneer |date=29 April 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"ZEE NEWS\">{{cite web |url=http://zeenews.india.com/news/nation/court-summons-sonia-gandhi-rahul-in-national-herald-land-grab-case_942922.html |title=Court summons Sonia Gandhi, Rahul in National Herald land grab case |publisher=ZEE NEWS |date=26 June 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/National-Herald-case-Delhi-HC-stays-criminal-proceedings-against-Sonia-Gandhi-Rahul-Gandhi/articleshow/39756755.cms |title=National Herald case: Delhi HC stays criminal proceedings against Sonia Gandhi, Rahul Gandhi |publisher=TIMES OF INDIA |date=6 August 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://zeenews.india.com/news/nation/national-herald-case-relief-for-sonia-rahul-delhi-hc-stays-summons-till-august-13_952910.html |title=National Herald case: Relief for Sonia, Rahul, Delhi HC stays summons till August 13 |publisher=ZEE NEWS |date=6 August 2014}}</ref> with the court observing [[prima facie]] evidence against all the accused.<ref name=\"ZEE NEWS\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/news/report/national-herald-case-what-you-should-know/20151209.htm |title=National Herald case: What you should know |publisher=[[Rediff.com]] |date=9 December 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://indianexpress.com/article/explained/national-herald-case-where-the-matter-stands/ |title=National Herald case explained: Everything you need to know |publisher=[[The Indian Express]] |date=10 December 2015}}</ref> On 1 August 2014 the [[Enforcement Directorate]] initiated probe to find any [[Money laundering#India|money laundering]] in the case<ref>{{cite web |url=http://zeenews.india.com/news/nation/national-herald-case-trouble-for-sonia-rahul-as-ed-begins-preliminary-probe_951680.html |title=National Herald case: Trouble for Sonia, Rahul as ED begins preliminary probe |publisher=ZEE NEWS |date=1 August 2014}}</ref> while on the same day Swamy was served notice by the High Court.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/national-herald-case-delhi-high-court-serves-notice-to-subramanian-swamy-congress-sonia-gandhi-rahul-gandhi/1/375130.html |title=National Herald case: Delhi High Court serves notice to Subramanian Swamy |publisher=INDIA TODAY |date=1 August 2014}}</ref> On 28 August the metropolitan court fixed 9 December for the next hearing of the case,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.firstpost.com/politics/national-herald-case-delhi-trial-court-to-hear-case-on-9-december-1686177.html |title=National Herald case: Delhi trial court to hear case on 9 December |publisher=FIRST POST |date=28 August 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.oneindia.com/india/court-defers-hearing-in-national-herald-case-1510868.html |title=Court defers hearing in National Herald case |publisher=ONE INDIA |date=28 August 2014}}</ref> while on 12 January 2015 the judge of the Delhi High Court recused himself from hearing the case stating that schedule of cases has been changed and directed that the petitions be directed before an appropriate bench.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-others/national-herald-case-judge-recuses-from-hearing-sonia-gandhi-rahul-gandhi-plea/ |title=National Herald case: Judge recuses from hearing Sonia Gandhi, Rahul Gandhi plea |publisher=THE INDIAN EXPRESS |date=12 January 2015}}</ref> On 27 January 2015, the Supreme Court asked Swamy to make out a case for the speedy trial in the Delhi High Court since the petition cannot be heard directly.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.firstpost.com/politics/national-herald-case-sc-directs-subramanian-swamy-approach-delhi-hc-2067027.html |title=National Herald case: SC directs Subramanian Swamy to approach Delhi HC |publisher=FIRST POST |date=27 January 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 September 2015 it was reported that the Enforcement Directorate had reopened the investigation.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.news18.com/news/politics/enforcement-directorate-reopens-national-herald-case-involving-sonia-and-rahul-gandhi-which-was-closed-in-august-1102471.html |title=Enforcement Directorate reopens National Herald case involving Sonia and Rahul Gandhi, which was closed in August |publisher=IBN Live |date=18 September 2015}}</ref> Following it, on 19 December 2015 Patiala House Court granted unconditional bail immediately on the hearing to all the five accused but one.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/gandhis-get-bail-in-herald-case/article8008532.ece |title=Sonia, Rahul get bail, hit out at Modi |newspaper=[[The Hindu]] |date=19 December 2015|last1=Kumar |first1=Nirnimesh |last2=Iqbal |first2=Mohammed |last3=Jeelani |first3=Mehboob }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://in.reuters.com/article/india-gandhis-sonia-rahul-congress-idINKBN0U208Z20151219 |title=Sonia, Rahul Gandhi get bail after rare court date over alleged fraud |publisher=Reuters India |date=19 December 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/india/live-national-herald-case-sonia-rahul-gandhi-to-appear-before-court-2157431 |title=National Herald case: Sonia, Rahul Gandhi immediately get bail; next hearing on February 20 |publisher=[[Daily News and Analysis]] |date=19 December 2015}}</ref> On 12 July 2016 the Delhi High Court set aside the trial court order of 11 January<ref>{{cite web |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/National-Herald-case-Relief-for-Congress/articleshow/53172103.cms |title=National Herald case: Relief for Congress |publisher=[[Times of India]] |date=12 July 2016}}</ref> and 11 March<ref>{{cite web |url=http://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-news-india/national-herald-case-delhi-court-asks-for-balance-sheets-of-ajl-congress/ |title=National Herald case: Delhi Court asks for balance sheets of AJL, Congress |publisher=[[The Indian Express]] |date=12 March 2016}}</ref> based on plea by Swamy to examine balance sheets of Congress party, [[Associated Journals Ltd|AJL]] and Young Indian from 2010-2013,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://delhihighcourt.nic.in/writereaddata/upload/Announcements/AnnouncementFile_BE5FNPPV.PDF |title=J- 2 PRONOUNCEMENT OF JUDGEMENTS(APPLET. JURISDICTION),1.CRL.M.C 671/2016,2.CRL.M.C. 672/2016, 3.CRL.M.C. 1317/2016, 4. CRL.M.C.1319/2016, 5. CRL.M.C.1321/2016 |publisher=[[Delhi High Court]] |date=12 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-news-india/national-herald-case-congress-hopes-delhi-high-court-ruling-will-end-bjp-subramanian-swamys-celebrations-2910408/ |title=National Herald case: Congress hopes Delhi High Court ruling will end BJP, Subramanian Swamy's celebrations |publisher=[[The Indian Express]] |date=12 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://zeenews.india.com/news/india/why-is-congress-so-afraid-of-national-herald-papers-will-re-apply-for-same-subramanian-swamy_1908050.html |title=Why is Congress so afraid of National Herald papers? Will re-apply for documents: Subramanian Swamy |publisher=[[Zee News]] |date=17 July 2016}}</ref> and fixed the date of next hearing on 20 August.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/pti-stories/will-file-fresh-application-in-herald-case-swamy-to-court-116071600485_1.html |title=Will file fresh application in National Herald case: Subramanian Swamy to court |publisher=[[Business Standard]] |date=16 July 2016}}</ref>\nCurrently, the case proceedings are on-going in Delhi High Court.<ref>https://www.livelaw.in/news-updates/i-have-no-documents-to-prove-that-rent-was-paid-to-young-india-152248</ref>\n\n===Temple Cases===\n====Nataraja temple case====\n\nSwamy had filed a petition in the Supreme Court with priests of the dikshithar sect challenging the decision of the [[Madras High Court]] on transferring the administration of the [[Thillai Nataraja Temple, Chidambaram|Nataraja temple]] to the then Tamil Nadu government in 2009.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ndtv.com/south/tamil-nadu-government-will-not-manage-famous-temple-rules-supreme-court-546936 |title=Tamil Nadu government will not manage famous temple, rules Supreme Court |author=J Sam Daniel Stalin |date=6 January 2014 |work=NDTV.com}}</ref>\n\nSwamy on referring to the provisions of Tamil Nadu Hindu Religious and Charitable Endowments Act, contended that [[Smarta Tradition|Podu Dikshitars]] have right to administer the temple<ref>{{cite web |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Nataraja-temple-to-be-managed-by-priest-not-by-Tamil-Nadu-govt/articleshow/28474693.cms |title=Nataraja temple to be managed by priest, not by Tamil Nadu govt |work=The Times of India}}</ref> and argued on handing over the administration on mismanagement grounds of temple's wealth is violation under article \n26 of the Constitution of India.<ref>http://judis.nic.in/supremecourt/imgs1.aspx?filename=41133</ref> On 6 January 2014 the Supreme Court ruled that the administration is to be handed over back to the priests of the temple from the state government.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/states/tamil_nadu/Nataraja-Temple-to-be-Managed-by-Priest-not-by-Tamil-Nadu-Government/2014/01/06/article1985968.ece#.UxyM0D-Syiw |title=Nataraja Temple to be Managed by Priest not by Tamil Nadu Government |work=The New Indian Express}}</ref>\n====Removing State control on Hindu temples====\nSubramanian Swamy filed a petition to remove  Kerala State government's control over Hindu temples by abolishing [[Devaswom boards in Kerala|Devaswom]]. In 2018, the Supreme Court agreed to examine the petition moved by him and TG Mohan Das to abolish Devaswom Board.The Supreme Court issued notice to the Kerala government and Devaswom Board of Travanacore and Cochin and sought their response in six weeks.<ref>http://www.newindianexpress.com/states/kerala/2018/oct/13/supreme-court-issues-notice-to-kerala-on-devaswom-board-1884903.html</ref> In 2019, the Kerala government opposed Subramanian Swamy's plea.<ref>https://wap.business-standard.com/article/pti-stories/kerala-opposes-swamy-s-plea-to-make-devaswom-boards-free-of-state-s-control-119012301349_1.html</ref>\n\n====Ayodhya temple case====\n\n{{Further|Ram Janmabhoomi}}\n{{Main|Ayodhya dispute}}\n\nOn 22 February 2016, Swamy filed a petition in the Supreme Court allowing construction of [[Rama]] temple at the disputed site where [[Demolition of the Babri Masjid|Babri Masjid was demolished]] in 1992, and expediting the adjudication related to order of the Allahabad High Court on 30 September 2010,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/article8268416.ece |title=Allow 'rebuilding' of Ram temple, Swamy urges SC |publisher=[[The Hindu]] |date=23 February 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/subramanian-swamy-moves-supreme-court-to-build-ram-temple-in-ayodhya/articleshow/51087635.cms |title=Subramanian Swamy moves Supreme Court to build Ram temple in Ayodhya |publisher=[[The Economic Times]] |date=23 February 2016}}</ref> petition was accepted on 26 February to be later heard by the court.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/sc-allows-swamys-plea-to-rebuild-ram-temple-along-with-ramjanmabhoomi-appeals/article8285368.ece |title=SC agrees to hear plea to 'rebuild' Ram temple |publisher=[[The Hindu]] |date=26 February 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Campaign against black money==\n{{see also|Black money in India}}\nSwamy founded the Action Committee Against Corruption in India (ACACI) on 14 October 2011 and acted as a chairperson. ACACI's goal is to take action against corruption in government and against [[Indian black money]] stashed abroad.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://indianexpress.com/tag/acaci/ |title=ACACI - The Indian Express |publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Swamy-announces-panel-against-corruption/articleshow/10355742.cms?referral=PM |title=Swamy announces panel against corruption |work=The Times of India}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.india.com/top-n/black-money-list-subramanian-swamy-lists-6-steps-to-bring-back-black-money-in-an-open-letter-to-narendra-modi-186813/ |title=Black Money List: Subramanian Swamy lists 6 steps to bring back black money in an open letter to Narendra Modi |author=Shikhar Jiwrajka |work=India.com}}</ref>\n\n==Views==\n\n===Foreign policy===\n==== China ====\n<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Deng Xioping with Subramanian Swamy 1981.jpg|thumb|right|[[Vice Chairman of the Communist Party of China]] [[Deng Xiaoping]] with Swamy at Great Hall of the People at Beijing in 1981.{{deletable image-caption|Tuesday, 10 October 2017|PROD}}]] -->\nSwamy has worked towards normalising [[Sino-Indian relations|relations between China and India]]. According to Swamy, the re-opening of the [[Mount Kailash#Religious significance|Kailash Mansarovar pilgrimage]] route was announced at a meeting convened by the People's Republic of China paramount leader [[Deng Xiaoping]] in April 1981, in which Swamy was in attendance. This meeting was widely reported in the media, although such claims have been contested by supporters of former Prime Minister [[Atal Bihari Vajpayee]].{{citation needed|date=December 2017}}\n\n==== Israel ====\nIn various speeches and articles, Swamy has expressed his admiration for, and solidarity with, the [[State of Israel]] and has credited its retaliatory capacity for its ability to survive as a nation in a hostile Arab environment. Swamy made pioneering efforts towards India's establishment of [[India\u2013Israel relations|diplomatic relations with Israel]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/first-israel-visas-from-india-were-issued-from-this-mps-residence/articleshow/59438603.cms |title=First Israel visas in India were issued from this MP's residence}}</ref> In 1982, Swamy became the first Indian political leader to make a well-publicised trip to Israel, where he met with several important Israeli leaders such as [[Yitzhak Rabin]] and then-Prime Minister [[Menachem Begin]]. His efforts at normalising relations with Israel have borne fruit with both India as well as Israels decision, in 1992, to facilitate the building of embassies in their respective countries.<ref name=\"Subramanian Swamy Party President\">{{cite web |url=http://janataparty.org/president.html |title=His Role in Foreign Affairs:The President |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121013034757/http://janataparty.org/president.html |archivedate=13 October 2012}}</ref>\n\n==== Sri Lanka and LTTE ====\nSwamy, on several occasions, has voiced support for the state of Sri Lanka in its role during [[Sri Lankan Civil War|Sri Lanka's protracted civil war with the LTTE]], for which he was criticised as \"pro Lanka\" by his political opponents domestically.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.news18.com/news/politics/india-shouldnt-support-resolution-against-lanka-swamy-454333.html |title=India shouldn't support resolution against Lanka: Swamy |work=IBNLive}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/sri-lankan-tamils-issue-karunanidhi-enacting-drama-says-jayalalithaa-dmk-pull-out-from-upa/1/258563.html |title=Karunanidhi enacting drama, says Jayalalithaa on DMK pull-out from UPA |publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sundayobserver.lk/2013/09/08/fea03.asp |title=Think as Sri Lankans first |publisher= |accessdate=25 July 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160506221510/http://www.sundayobserver.lk/2013/09/08/fea03.asp |archivedate=6 May 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://zeenews.india.com/news/nation/swamy-slams-dmk-chief-for-remarks-on-indo-sri-lankan-relations_793425.html |title=Swamy slams DMK chief for remarks on Indo-Sri Lankan relations |work=Zee News}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/india/subramanian-swamy-attacked-by-lawyers-in-madras-hc/story-KiCd6SNSbJ9pIT8a3mW0QN.html |title=Subramanian Swamy attacked by lawyers in Madras HC |publisher=[[Hindustan Times]]}}</ref> In an interview given to ''[[The Sunday Leader]]'' newspaper, Swamy stated that the Indian government should attend the [[CHOGM]] meeting held in [[Colombo]] despite stiff opposition from Indian politicians in Tamil Nadu concerned for the welfare and human rights of Tamils in Sri Lanka, placing the onus on the LTTE for human rights violations during the Sri Lankan civil war,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thesundayleader.lk/2013/11/03/india-must-ignore-lttes-financial-orphans-dr-subramanium-swamy/ |title=India Must Ignore LTTE's Financial Orphans \u2013 Dr Subramanium Swamy |publisher=}}</ref><ref>[http://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/pm-may-skip-chogm-meet-due-to-opposition/article1-1148937.aspx] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131111051031/http://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/pm-may-skip-chogm-meet-due-to-opposition/article1-1148937.aspx|date=11 November 2013}}</ref> he had favoured [[Mahinda Rajapaksa]] also  during [[2015 Sri Lankan presidential election|Sri Lanka 2015 election]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://zeenews.india.com/news/nation/give-rajapaksa-bharat-ratna-for-wiping-out-ltte_757861.html |title=Give Rajapaksa Bharat Ratna for wiping out LTTE |publisher=ZEE NEWS |date=11 February 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Tamil-activists-burn-Subramanian-Swamys-effigy-after-he-demands-Bharat-Ratna-for-Rajapaksa/articleshow/44899410.cms |title=Tamil activists burn Subramanian Swamy's effigy after he demands Bharat Ratna for Rajapaksa |publisher=TIMES OF INDIA |date=21 October 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.itnnews.lk/local-news/large-fraction-of-tamils-will-vote-for-president-rajapaksa-subramaniam-swamy/ |title=Large fraction of Tamils will vote for President Rajapaksa \u2013 Subramaniam Swamy |publisher=itnnews.lk |date=28 November 2014 |access-date=13 August 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160823030745/http://www.itnnews.lk/local-news/large-fraction-of-tamils-will-vote-for-president-rajapaksa-subramaniam-swamy/ |archive-date=23 August 2016 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n==== United States ====\nSwamy is a strong supporter of U.S. President [[Donald Trump]], endorsing Trump's presidential candidacy in 2016 and comparing Trump to himself.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2016-05-24/modi-s-bet-on-trump-of-india-signals-risks-to-his-reform-push |title=Modi's Bet on 'Trump of India' Signals Risks to Reform Push |work=[[Bloomberg News|Bloomberg]] |date=May 24, 2016}}</ref>\n\nAfter the [[Unite the Right rally|Charlottesville riots]] in August 2017, he posted a tweet urging Indians residing in the United States to \"stand with Trump at this hour of his being hunted by cockeyed liberals & Left wing loonies on racism\" and praised Trump for \"having showed the hypocrites their place by telling it like it is.\"<ref>https://www.thequint.com/neon/social-buzz/subramanian-swamy-trolled-on-twitter</ref>\n\nFollowing criticism of Pakistan by Trump, Swamy called for closer relations between India and the United States.<ref>http://www.freepressjournal.in/india/after-us-president-trumps-anti-pak-tweet-subramanian-swamy-calls-for-stronger-india-us-relations/1197599</ref>\n\n===Domestic policy===\n==== Kashmir ====\nIn September 2008, Swamy stridently retorted against the contentions of some Indian columnists who voiced their opinions in favor of \"peacefully\" surrendering Kashmir to Pakistan. He said,\n\n:\"I would say that the silent suffering majority of India wants none of this. The 'Kashmir issue,' in fact, can no more be solved by dialogue either with the Pakistanis or the Hurriyat, leave alone the constitutional impossibility of allowing it to secede. [...]Kashmir, in fact, is now our [[History of Kashmir|defining identity]]. It is a touchstone for our resolve to preserve our national integrity. The population of that State may be majority Muslim but the land and its history is predominantly Hindu. For our commitment to the survival of the ancient civilisation of India and the composite culture that secularists talk of, we have not only to win that coming inevitable war but also resolve never to part with Kashmir. [...]\n\n:Pakistanis often cite the United Nations resolutions on Kashmir to argue for a plebiscite. This obfuscates the fact of accession of the State to India. The legality of the Instrument of Accession signed in favour of India by the then Maharaja of J&K, Hari Singh, on 26 October 1947 has to prevail anyway.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-opinion/article1345324.ece |location=Chennai, India |work=The Hindu |title=Kashmir defines Indian identity |date=25 September 2008}}</ref>\n\n==== Tamil Nadu politics ====\nSwamy is well known for his critical views against the \"Aryan versus Dravidian\" politics of [[Periyar E. V. Ramasamy]], calling it as the theory forwarded by the British.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hindu.com/2011/06/18/stories/2011061862200200.htm |title=Tamil Nadu / Madurai News : \"Caste not birth-based\" |work=The Hindu |date=18 June 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130806095535/http://www.hindu.com/2011/06/18/stories/2011061862200200.htm |archivedate=6 August 2013 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> He has been a staunch opponent of the armed rebel group [[Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam]].<ref>{{cite news |agency=Press Trust of India |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Janata-Party-chief-Subramanian-Swamy-appears-before-tribunal-examining-LTTE-ban/articleshow/6828953.cms?referral=PM |title=Janata Party chief Subramanian Swamy appears before tribunal examining LTTE ban |work=The Times of India |date=28 October 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/ltte-part-of-the-problem-swamy/article1375090.ece |title=LTTE part of the problem: Swamy |work=The Hindu |date=13 November 2008}}</ref><ref>[http://www.epdpnews.com/articals_content.php?artiid=24&artiname=Subramanian%20Swamy%20addresses%20the%20Sri%20Lankan%20Diaspora%20in%20Toronto&ln=eng] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120510114143/http://www.epdpnews.com/articals_content.php?artiid=24&artiname=Subramanian%20Swamy%20addresses%20the%20Sri%20Lankan%20Diaspora%20in%20Toronto&ln=eng|date=10 May 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/nation/article157835.ece |title=Swamy criticises Karuna's statement on refugees |publisher=NEW INDIAN EXPRESS |date=16 May 2012}}</ref>\nHe also urged the Indian government not to support the US led resolution condemning [[Alleged war crimes during the final stages of the Sri Lankan Civil War|war crimes]] in the [[Sri Lankan Civil War]], citing it as one-sided and not in the interest of India.<ref>{{cite news |agency=Press Trust of India |url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2013-03-08/news/37561573_1_subramanian-swamy-unhrc-rajapaksa |title=Subramanian Swamy asks US to work with Sri Lanka on resolution at UNHRC |work=The Economic Times |date=8 March 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://channelone.co.in/India/india-should-not-support-resolution-against-sri-lanka--subramanian-swamy-839.html |title=India should not support resolution against Sri Lanka: Subramanian Swamy |publisher=Channel One |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131109124814/http://channelone.co.in/India/india-should-not-support-resolution-against-sri-lanka--subramanian-swamy-839.html |archivedate=9 November 2013}}</ref> Swamy moved the court and got the order restoring quota for [[Sri Lankan Tamil people|Sri Lankan Tamil]] refugees in colleges in the state.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/states/tamil_nadu/Higher-Education-Remains-a-Struggle-for-Refugees/2014/06/22/article2293215.ece |title=Higher Education Remains a Struggle for Refugees |publisher=NEW INDIAN EXPRESS |date=22 June 2014}}</ref>\n\nSwamy obtained [[Supreme Court of India|Supreme Court]] Stay against the implementation of [[Sethusamudram Shipping Canal Project]] (SSCP). He believes that it would hurt the sentiments of people who believe that this shallow land connecting between [[Tamil Nadu]] and [[Sri Lanka]] was built by Lord [[Rama]]. He strongly opposes the implementation of SSCP citing that implementing this scheme will be a criminal offence under section 295 [[Indian Penal Code]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/india/report_ram-setu-project-is-illegal-arbitrary-and-unacceptable-subramanian-swamy_1804422 |title=Ram Setu project is illegal, arbitrary and unacceptable: Subramanian Swamy |agency=ANI |date=25 February 2013 |accessdate=23 July 2013 |publisher=DNA}}</ref><ref>[http://www.indlaw.com/guest/DisplayNews.aspx?FCD913AA-4308-4C14-9B32-F8696B16303F] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140303155432/http://www.indlaw.com/guest/DisplayNews.aspx?FCD913AA-4308-4C14-9B32-F8696B16303F|date=3 March 2014}}</ref> He wrote letters to Prime Minister of India in June 2009 asking him to stop the project<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tamil.oneindia.com/news/2009/06/18/tn-hold-sethu-project-implementation-says-swamy.html |title=Hold Sethu project implementation, says Swamy, \u0b9a\u0bc7\u0ba4\u0bc1.. '\u0bb9\u0bcb\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bcd \u0b86\u0ba9\u0bcd': \u0b9a\u0bbe\u0bae\u0bbf |publisher=OneIndia Tamil |language=Tamil |date=18 June 2009 |accessdate=16 October 2011}}</ref> and had informed the Supreme Court on 14 October 2015 that the government may not continue with the [[Sethusamudram Shipping Canal Project|Sethusamudram Project]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/govt-decided-not-to-touch-ram-sethu-subramanian-swamy-tells-supreme-court/article7758406.ece |title=Govt. decided not to \"touch\" Ram Sethu, Swamy tells SC |publisher=[[The Hindu|THE HINDU]] |date=14 October 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Anti-Muslim views ===\nIn response to the [[2011 Mumbai bombings]], he wrote an editorial in ''[[Daily News and Analysis]]'' (''DNA'') where he called for the demolition of mosques and for the disenfranchisement of Muslims unless \"acknowledge that their ancestors were Hindus\".<ref name=\":0\" /> \nSome of Swamy's suggestions in the article are:\n\n*The Hindu is the target and that Muslims of India are being programmed by a slow reactive process to become radical and thus slide into suicide against Hindus.\n*Remove Article 370, and re-settle ex-servicemen in the Valley. Create Panun Kashmir for Hindu Pandit community. Look or create opportunity to take over PoK. If Pakistan continues to back terrorists, assist the Baluchis and Sindhis to struggle for independence.\n*Enact a national law prohibiting conversion from Hindu religion to any other religion.\n*Only Muslims who \"acknowledge that their ancestors were Hindus\" be allowed to vote in India.<ref>{{citation |author=Subramanian Swamy |date=16 July 2011 |accessdate=27 July 2011 |title=Analysis: How to wipe out Islamic terror |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/analysis/analysis_how-to-wipe-out-islamic-terror_1566203-all |work=[[DNA (newspaper)|DNA]] |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110818232314/http://www.dnaindia.com/analysis/analysis_how-to-wipe-out-islamic-terror_1566203-all |archivedate=18 August 2011}}</ref>\n\nSwamy had written a similar column in ''[[The New Indian Express]]'' after the [[2008 Mumbai attacks]].  As a result of his \"reprehensible\" views in the articles, [[Harvard University]] cancelled two economics courses taught at the university by Swamy.<ref name=BBCNews20150628>\n{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-india-16081751 |title=Harvard drops Indian MP Subramanian Swamy's courses |publisher=BBC News |date=December 8, 2011 |accessdate=2015-06-28}}</ref><ref name=\":1\" />\n\nOn 3 August 2011 the [[National Commission for Minorities]] decided to file civil charges against Swamy for the article and promoting on the basis of religion.<ref>{{cite web |author=Vidya Subrahmaniam |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/minorities-commission-to-press-criminal-charges-against-swamy/article2317169.ece |title=Minorities' commission to press criminal charges against Swamy |work=The Hindu |date=3 August 2011}}</ref> On 4 October 2011 the [[Delhi Police]] registered the case.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/case-against-swamy/article2510624.ece |title=Case against Swamy |work=The Hindu |date=4 October 2011}}</ref> Swamy was then granted police protection by the [[Delhi High Court]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/swamy-gets-interim-protection/article2800800.ece |title=Swamy gets interim protection |work=The Hindu |date=14 January 2012}}</ref> On 30 January 2012 Swamy was granted [[anticipatory bail]] by the court with the condition that he would not write such articles in the future.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Subramanian-Swamy-granted-anticipatory-bail-in-inflammatory-article-case/articleshow/11684787.cms |title=Subramanian Swamy granted anticipatory bail in 'inflammatory' article case |work=The Times of India |date=30 January 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nSwamy met Roxna Kapadia, whose father was member of [[Indian Civil Service (British India)]] and an Indian lady of [[Parsi]] ethnicity who was studying PhD in mathematics at [[Harvard University]].<ref>{{cite web |author=Elizabeth Roche |url=http://www.livemint.com/Leisure/J7Ot7WsW7O8cytA908g5zJ/Perfect-copetitioners.html |title=Perfect co-petitioners |publisher=Livemint |date=8 February 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"Roxna Swamy Interview\">{{cite web |title=The well-regarded Supreme Court advocate on her husband : SUNIT ARORA INTERVIEWS ROXNA SWAMY |url=http://www.outlookindia.com/magazine/story/his-views-are-those-of-a-patriotic-indian/279891 |work=[[Outlook (Indian magazine)|Outlook]] |accessdate=3 January 2012}}</ref> They were married in June 1966. Swamys have two daughters. The elder daughter, Gitanjali Swamy, is an entrepreneur and private equity professional. She is married to [[Sanjay Sarma]], a professor at [[MIT]], who is the son of E.A.S Sarma, a retired [[IAS officer]] and former secretary Economic Affairs to the government of India. The younger daughter, Suhasini Haidar, is a print and television journalist married to Nadeem Haidar, the son of former Indian Foreign Secretary [[Salman Haider|Salman Haidar]].{{citation needed|date=February 2017}}\n\n==Honours and awards==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%;\"\n|-\n! Year !! Name !! Awarding organisation !! Ref.\n|-\n| 2012\n| Distinguished Alumni Award.\n| [[Hindu College, University of Delhi]].\n|<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/article2799252.ece |title=It's time silent majority spoke up, says Vinod Rai |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=22 June 2012 |location=Chennai, India |date=14 January 2012}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2016\n| Tamil Ratna\n| America Tamil Sangam\n|<ref>[http://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-news-india/subramanian-swamy-awarded-tamil-ratna-in-united-states/ Subramanian Swamy awarded \u2018Tamil Ratna\u2019 in United States]</ref>\n|}\n\n==Books, research papers and journals==\nSwamy is the author of several books, research papers and journals. A complete list of papers, books and journals authored by him is given below. He has also co-authored with [[Paul Samuelson]], a paper on the Theory of Index Numbers (American Economic Review, 1974) and another in the Royal Economic Society\u2019s Economic Journal (1984).<ref name=\"Swamy Samuelson\"/>\n\n===Books===\n* ''Hindutva and National Renaissance'' (Publisher: Har Anand Publication; {{ISBN|978-81-241-1527-5}})\n* ''Virat Hindu Identity - Concept and its Power'' (Publisher: Har Anand Publication; {{ISBN|978-81-241-1770-5}})\n* ''Economic Growth in China and India, 1952\u201370'' (Publisher: University of Chicago Press; {{ISBN|978-0-226-78315-4}})\n* ''Indian economic planning: An alternative approach'' (Publisher: Barnes & Noble / Vikas publications ; {{ISBN|978-0-389-04202-0}})\n* ''Building a New India: An Agenda for National Renaissance'' (Publisher: UBS PUBLISHERS' AND DISTRIBUTORS LTD; {{ISBN|978-81-85674-21-6}})\n* ''India's Labour Standards and the WTO Framework'' (Publisher: Konark Publishers; {{ISBN|978-81-220-0585-1}})\n* ''India's economic performance and reforms: A perspective for the new millennium'' (Publisher: Konark Publishers; {{ISBN|978-81-220-0594-3}})\n* ''Assassination of Rajiv Gandhi: Unanswered Questions and Unasked Queries'' (Publisher: Konark Publishers; {{ISBN|978-81-220-0591-2}})\n* ''India's China perspective'' (Publisher: Konark Publishers; {{ISBN|978-81-220-0606-3}})\n* ''Financial Architecture and Economic Development in China and India'' (Publisher: Konark Publishers; {{ISBN|978-81-220-0718-3}})\n* ''Trade and Industry in Japan: A Guide to Indian Entrepreneurs and Businessmen'' (Publisher: Prentice-Hall of India; {{ISBN|978-81-203-0785-8}})\n* ''Sri Lanka in Crisis: India's Options'' (Publisher: Har Anand Publications; {{ISBN|978-81-241-1260-1}})\n* ''Kailas and Manasarovar after 22 years in Shiva's domain'' (Publisher: Allied Publishers)\n* ''Hindus Under Siege'' (Publisher: Har Anand Publications; {{ISBN|978-81-241-1207-6}})\n* ''Rama Setu: Symbol of National Unity'' (Publisher: Har Anand Publications; {{ISBN|978-81-241-1418-6}})\n* ''Terrorism in India: A Strategy of Deterrence for India's National Security'' (Publisher: Har Anand Publications; {{ISBN|978-81-241-1344-8}})\n* ''Corruption and Corporate Governance in India: Satyam, Spectrum & Sundaram'' (Publisher: Har Anand Publications; {{ISBN|978-81-241-1486-5}})\n* ''2G Spectrum Scam'' (Publisher: Har Anand Publications; {{ISBN|978-81-241-1638-8}})\n* ''Electronic Voting Machines: Unconstitutional and Tamperable'' (Publisher: Vision Books; {{ISBN|978-81-7094-798-1}})\n* ''Predictions and Meditations'' (Publisher: India International Centre Quarterly 36, no. 3/4 (2009): 202-22. https://www.jstor.org/stable/23006413.\n* ''[https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/38589813-the-ideology-of-india-s-modern-right The Ideology of India\u2019s Modern Right]'' (Publisher: Har Anand Publication; {{ISBN| 978-8124118924}})\n* ''[https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/48070396-reset RESET: Regaining India\u2019s Economic Legacy]'' (Publisher: Rupa Publications; {{ISBN|978-93-5333-651-6}}) RESET was top selling new [[E-book|eBook]] of 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/books-and-literature/ebooks-which-sold-most-this-amish-tripathi-devdutt-pattanaik-year-amazon-6191464/|title=The year that was: eBooks which sold most this year|date=2019-12-31|website=The Indian Express|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-01}}</ref>\n\n===Articles===\n*  \"Can India make it? India's path to sustained growth\" (Publisher: Harvard Asia Pacific review, Volumes 6\u20138 by Harvard University. Dept. of East Asian Languages and Civilizations, 2002)\n*  \"The response to economic challenge: A comparative economic history of China and India\", 1870\u20131952 (Publisher: The Quarterly Journal of Economics, Volume 93 by Harvard University by the MIT Press, 1979)\n\n===Research papers===\n* Economic growth and income distribution in a developing nation (Publisher: Harvard University, 1965)\n* Nuclear policy for India (Publisher: Bharatiya Jana Sangh Publication, 1968)\n* Plan for full employment (Publisher: Bharatiya Jana Sangh, 1970)\n* Theoretical aspects of index numbers (Publisher: Harvard Institute of Economic Research, 1985)\n* Land reforms: an economist's approach (Publisher: Deendayal Research Institute)\n* Samuelson, P., & Swamy, S. (1974). Invariant Economic Index Numbers and Canonical Duality: Survey and Synthesis. The American Economic Review, 64(4), 566-593. https://www.jstor.org/stable/1813311\n* Swamy, Subramanian. \"On Samuelson's Conjecture.\" Indian Economic Review, New Series, 5, no. 2 (1970): 169-75. https://www.jstor.org/stable/23294448\n* Swamy, S. (1965). Consistency of Fisher's Tests. Econometrica, 33(3), 619-623. doi:1. https://www.jstor.org/stable/1911757 doi:1\n* Swamy, S. (1963). Notes on Fractile Graphical Analysis. Econometrica, 31(3), 551-554. doi:1. https://www.jstor.org/stable/1909994 doi:1\n* Swamy, S. (1969). Optimal Allocation of Investment in A Two-sector Model with Foreign Aid. Indian Economic Review, 4(1), new series, 35-44. https://www.jstor.org/stable/23294380\n* Swamy, S. (1969). Systems Analysis of Strategic Defence Needs: A Sequel. Economic and Political Weekly, 4(18), 772-772. https://www.jstor.org/stable/40739578\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n* {{official website|http://swamy39.blogspot.in}}\n*[http://loksabhaph.nic.in/writereaddata/biodata_1_12/2614.htm Official biographical sketch in Parliament of India website]\n{{Bharatiya Janata Party}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Swamy, Subramanian}}\n[[Category:1939 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Bharatiya Janata Party politicians from Tamil Nadu]]\n[[Category:Bharatiya Jana Sangh politicians]]\n[[Category:Janata Party politicians]]\n[[Category:Politicians from Chennai]]\n[[Category:Indian Hindus]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian economists]]\n[[Category:Tamil Nadu politicians]]\n[[Category:6th Lok Sabha members]]\n[[Category:7th Lok Sabha members]